1
00:02:49,922 --> 00:02:51,173
Come, come!

2
00:02:55,636 --> 00:02:56,720
Please! Please!

3
00:03:11,568 --> 00:03:13,487
Aziz.

4
00:03:13,737 --> 00:03:14,780
Aziz.

5
00:03:17,699 --> 00:03:19,076
Aziz, light!

6
00:03:20,661 --> 00:03:21,703
Aziz, light.

7
00:03:23,789 --> 00:03:25,165
Good.

8
00:03:26,375 --> 00:03:27,918
We start again.

9
00:03:29,336 --> 00:03:33,715
"When the three planets are in eclipse,
the black hole, like a door, is open.

10
00:03:33,882 --> 00:03:35,759
Evil comes...

11
00:03:35,926 --> 00:03:38,178
...spreading terror and chaos."

12
00:03:38,345 --> 00:03:41,807
See the snake, Billy? The ultimate evil.

13
00:03:41,974 --> 00:03:44,935
- Make sure you get the snake.
- Yes, I've got your snakes.

14
00:03:45,102 --> 00:03:46,603
I got all the snakes.

15
00:03:46,770 --> 00:03:48,939
So when is this snake act
supposed to occur?

16
00:03:49,940 --> 00:03:52,734
Well, if this is the five...

17
00:03:52,901 --> 00:03:54,903
...and this is the one...

18
00:03:59,783 --> 00:04:01,410
Every 5000 years.

19
00:04:02,494 --> 00:04:05,289
So I've got some time, then.

20
00:04:13,338 --> 00:04:15,299
You bring them water.

21
00:04:15,465 --> 00:04:17,634
Good boy. I will take it to them.

22
00:04:17,801 --> 00:04:20,470
Go with God. Be safe from evil.

23
00:04:21,805 --> 00:04:25,475
You see here these different peoples,
or symbols of people...

24
00:04:25,642 --> 00:04:30,397
...gathering together the four elements
of life: water, fire, earth, air...

25
00:04:30,564 --> 00:04:32,691
...around a fifth one.

26
00:04:32,858 --> 00:04:34,318
A fifth...

27
00:04:35,277 --> 00:04:36,320
...element.

28
00:04:39,990 --> 00:04:41,658
Forgive me, lord.

29
00:04:41,825 --> 00:04:44,286
They already know too much.

30
00:04:48,498 --> 00:04:49,541
Father.

31
00:04:49,958 --> 00:04:51,084
Yes, how are you today?

32
00:04:51,251 --> 00:04:53,378
- Very well. You have some glasses?
- Of course.

33
00:04:53,545 --> 00:04:56,673
Father, I'm so glad to see you.
It's the most extraordinary thing.

34
00:04:56,840 --> 00:04:59,176
I mean, look.
It's the greatest find in history.

35
00:04:59,343 --> 00:05:01,511
Yes. You must be parched.

36
00:05:02,763 --> 00:05:05,057
Oh, yes, yes. I'm sorry.

37
00:05:07,184 --> 00:05:09,061
I mean, it's like a battle plan.

38
00:05:09,227 --> 00:05:12,189
Here, the good. Here, the evil.

39
00:05:12,522 --> 00:05:16,860
And here, a weapon against evil.

40
00:05:18,612 --> 00:05:20,656
I'm going to be famous.

41
00:05:20,822 --> 00:05:23,784
Then-- Then let us toast to your fame.

42
00:05:25,035 --> 00:05:26,870
To fame.

43
00:05:32,084 --> 00:05:35,671
You can't drink a toast with water.
Billy, in my sack, the grappa.

44
00:05:35,837 --> 00:05:36,964
Yes.

45
00:05:48,141 --> 00:05:49,893
This I don't understand. But this...

46
00:05:50,060 --> 00:05:51,561
...this could be something...

47
00:05:52,062 --> 00:05:53,730
...prehistoric.

48
00:05:53,897 --> 00:05:55,232
Maybe? I don't know.

49
00:05:56,525 --> 00:05:58,694
But wait.

50
00:05:58,860 --> 00:06:01,697
Here. Here.

51
00:06:08,161 --> 00:06:09,997
Look, look.

52
00:06:20,382 --> 00:06:22,009
They're here.

53
00:06:27,097 --> 00:06:29,016
This man...

54
00:06:29,182 --> 00:06:32,019
...this perfect being.

55
00:06:32,185 --> 00:06:34,271
I know this is the key. I know it.

56
00:06:40,610 --> 00:06:42,779
This divine light they talk about.

57
00:06:42,946 --> 00:06:45,449
What is divine light?

58
00:06:46,366 --> 00:06:47,576
Aziz, light!

59
00:06:49,661 --> 00:06:51,496
Much better. Thank you, Aziz.

60
00:07:08,221 --> 00:07:09,806
My lord.

61
00:07:52,015 --> 00:07:55,977
Father, this is the most
unbelievable thing I have ever seen.

62
00:07:56,144 --> 00:07:57,270
Don't you think...?

63
00:08:02,067 --> 00:08:04,653
Are you German?

64
00:08:07,239 --> 00:08:10,784
Lord, I know he was about
to discover everything.

65
00:08:10,951 --> 00:08:13,995
But there is no worry.
I was there in time.

66
00:08:14,162 --> 00:08:17,040
Priest, you and those before you...

67
00:08:17,207 --> 00:08:19,501
...have served us well.

68
00:08:19,668 --> 00:08:21,586
But war is coming.

69
00:08:21,753 --> 00:08:25,799
Stones not safe on Earth anymore.

70
00:08:42,107 --> 00:08:43,817
This...

71
00:08:43,984 --> 00:08:45,777
...is really amazing.

72
00:09:17,142 --> 00:09:19,019
The fifth element.

73
00:09:20,979 --> 00:09:23,190
Take the stones.

74
00:10:03,355 --> 00:10:04,689
My lord...

75
00:10:04,856 --> 00:10:08,485
...if you take the weapon, we will
be defenseless when the evil returns.

76
00:10:08,652 --> 00:10:13,573
In 300 years, when evil returns...

77
00:10:13,740 --> 00:10:15,533
...so shall we.

78
00:10:23,375 --> 00:10:24,918
Oh, professor.

79
00:10:25,961 --> 00:10:27,420
Professor.

80
00:10:33,885 --> 00:10:35,512
Don't move!

81
00:10:36,429 --> 00:10:37,889
- I-- I have a gun!
- Billy.

82
00:10:38,056 --> 00:10:41,434
Please, understand.
They're our friends.

83
00:10:41,601 --> 00:10:42,852
Friends?

84
00:10:43,019 --> 00:10:46,398
Father, they've killed the professor.
They're monsters.

85
00:10:46,564 --> 00:10:48,525
I'll explain everything. Billy...

86
00:10:49,025 --> 00:10:50,777
- You're with them?
- Billy, look at me.

87
00:10:50,944 --> 00:10:52,195
I am your friend.

88
00:10:52,362 --> 00:10:54,781
- No, Father.
- Billy, look at me!

89
00:10:54,948 --> 00:10:59,035
Please, put the gun down.

90
00:10:59,202 --> 00:11:00,537
No.

91
00:11:00,870 --> 00:11:02,330
Billy, no!

92
00:11:08,962 --> 00:11:11,256
Hurry! The wall is closing!

93
00:11:11,423 --> 00:11:13,300
Here is your mission now:

94
00:11:13,466 --> 00:11:17,262
Pass your knowledge to the next priest
as it was passed on to you.

95
00:11:17,429 --> 00:11:21,057
I will do as you command, but please,
hurry, you still have time.

96
00:11:21,224 --> 00:11:23,268
Time not important.

97
00:11:23,435 --> 00:11:26,521
Only life important.

98
00:11:39,743 --> 00:11:42,120
I will fulfill my mission!

99
00:11:42,287 --> 00:11:43,913
You can count on me!

100
00:11:47,751 --> 00:11:50,503
I will pass the knowledge
until your return!

101
00:12:12,400 --> 00:12:15,153
Deploy intership stabilizer.
Power capacitors: check.

102
00:12:19,407 --> 00:12:20,700
- Anything yet?
- No, sir.

103
00:12:20,867 --> 00:12:23,244
- Not even a temperature?
- The analyzers have jammed.

104
00:12:23,411 --> 00:12:25,789
One shows a million degrees,
the others minus 5000.

105
00:12:26,664 --> 00:12:28,124
Let's see it.

106
00:12:44,933 --> 00:12:46,810
It's taking shape.

107
00:13:05,161 --> 00:13:06,579
Send out a probe.

108
00:13:07,831 --> 00:13:11,042
Ladies and gentlemen, the president
of the Federated Territories.

109
00:13:14,838 --> 00:13:17,424
On air with General Staedert
in 30 seconds.

110
00:13:24,639 --> 00:13:28,143
Oh, I saved this seat for you, Father.

111
00:13:29,686 --> 00:13:32,439
- President on the line.
- We're in position, Mr. President.

112
00:13:32,605 --> 00:13:35,692
I have to address the Supreme Council.
Just the facts, general.

113
00:13:35,859 --> 00:13:38,611
No results from the chemical
and molecular analysis yet.

114
00:13:38,778 --> 00:13:40,196
All the calibers are overshot.

115
00:13:40,363 --> 00:13:42,198
<i>We're initiating
thermonucleatic imaging.</i>

116
00:13:42,365 --> 00:13:45,034
So, what you're saying is,
you don't know what this is.

117
00:13:45,201 --> 00:13:47,620
Not yet. All we know is
it just keeps getting bigger.

118
00:13:47,787 --> 00:13:48,830
Recommendation?

119
00:13:48,997 --> 00:13:52,041
My philosophy is shoot first
and ask questions later.

120
00:13:52,208 --> 00:13:54,586
I don't like uninvited guests.

121
00:13:54,752 --> 00:13:57,213
- All right, then, Staedert--
- Mr. President?

122
00:13:59,007 --> 00:14:01,301
- Yes?
<i>- Priest Vito Cornelius...</i>

123
00:14:01,468 --> 00:14:03,720
<i>...expert of astrophenomenon.</i>

124
00:14:03,887 --> 00:14:08,683
I have a different theory
to offer you, sir.

125
00:14:08,850 --> 00:14:10,143
You have 20 seconds.

126
00:14:16,649 --> 00:14:18,359
Imagine for a moment that this...

127
00:14:18,526 --> 00:14:21,279
...thing is not anything
that can be identified...

128
00:14:21,446 --> 00:14:24,240
...because it prefers not to be.

129
00:14:24,407 --> 00:14:28,411
Wherever there is life,
it brings death...

130
00:14:29,078 --> 00:14:32,916
- ...because it is evil. Absolute evil.
- One more reason to shoot first.

131
00:14:33,082 --> 00:14:35,752
Evil begets evil, Mr. President.

132
00:14:35,919 --> 00:14:38,421
Shooting will only make it stronger.

133
00:14:42,634 --> 00:14:44,928
Probe will attain its objective
in five seconds.

134
00:14:49,766 --> 00:14:51,392
Growth rate is at 27 percent.

135
00:14:51,559 --> 00:14:54,437
Your theory is interesting, Father,
but we don't have time.

136
00:14:54,604 --> 00:14:58,107
Time is of no importance, Mr. President.
Only life is important.

137
00:14:58,274 --> 00:15:00,693
You're right.
That's exactly what we're gonna do.

138
00:15:00,860 --> 00:15:03,947
We're gonna protect the life of
200 billion of my fellow citizens.

139
00:15:04,113 --> 00:15:05,657
General, you may fire when ready.

140
00:15:05,823 --> 00:15:08,993
Up-front loading of a 120-ZR missile.
Marker lights on the objective.

141
00:15:15,041 --> 00:15:16,918
Its structure solidified on the surface.

142
00:15:17,085 --> 00:15:20,880
I think it's anticipating the attack.
Anticipation denotes intelligence.

143
00:15:21,047 --> 00:15:25,093
The most terrible intelligence
imaginable, Mr. President.

144
00:15:28,179 --> 00:15:30,265
One-twenty's loaded.

145
00:15:30,431 --> 00:15:34,143
The ship is in combat formation.
Missiles are loaded, Mr. President.

146
00:15:34,310 --> 00:15:36,312
- Staedert.
<i>- Yes, sir.</i>

147
00:15:36,479 --> 00:15:39,148
- I have a doubt.
- I don't, Mr. President.

148
00:15:49,409 --> 00:15:51,035
Staedert.

149
00:15:51,202 --> 00:15:53,162
What happened?
Staedert, can you hear me?

150
00:15:53,329 --> 00:15:55,081
Staedert? What happened, Staedert?

151
00:15:55,248 --> 00:15:57,834
<i>- Did you destroy it?</i>
- I'm about to, sir.

152
00:16:03,673 --> 00:16:06,551
The planet has increased
in diameter by 200 percent.

153
00:16:06,718 --> 00:16:08,052
It's moving towards the ship.

154
00:16:13,516 --> 00:16:15,685
What-- What do we have
that's bigger than 240?

155
00:16:15,852 --> 00:16:17,604
Nothing, sir.

156
00:16:18,021 --> 00:16:21,733
Staedert, do you hear me?
Get out of there.

157
00:16:22,150 --> 00:16:25,194
I don't want an incident.
Do you hear me, Staedert?

158
00:16:25,361 --> 00:16:28,531
<i>Get out of there.
Can you hear me, Staedert?</i>

159
00:16:28,698 --> 00:16:30,617
<i>Do you understand? Listen.</i>

160
00:16:30,783 --> 00:16:33,328
This is the president. That's an order.

161
00:16:35,538 --> 00:16:38,124
<i>Do you understand me?
Do you hear me?</i>

162
00:16:38,291 --> 00:16:42,253
<i>- Get out of there! Answer me!</i>
- Good God.

163
00:17:05,234 --> 00:17:06,986
<i>Four a day.</i>

164
00:17:19,582 --> 00:17:21,334
I'm trying.

165
00:17:21,751 --> 00:17:23,503
<i>To quit is my goal.</i>

166
00:17:26,673 --> 00:17:29,133
Hey, hey, hey.

167
00:17:29,300 --> 00:17:30,968
I'm up.

168
00:17:33,262 --> 00:17:34,764
All right. I'm up.

169
00:17:34,931 --> 00:17:36,683
God.

170
00:17:37,100 --> 00:17:38,976
Yeah, yeah.

171
00:17:39,185 --> 00:17:41,104
- Yes?
<i>- Hey, dog brain, Finger here.</i>

172
00:17:42,313 --> 00:17:44,273
- Hi, sweetie.
<i>- I love you too, major.</i>

173
00:17:44,440 --> 00:17:46,818
<i>But you haven't called me that
since basic training.</i>

174
00:17:46,984 --> 00:17:50,196
- I was talking to the cat.
<i>- Oh, yeah, I forgot...</i>

175
00:17:50,363 --> 00:17:52,949
<i>...you still prefer your cat
to the real thing.</i>

176
00:17:53,116 --> 00:17:54,617
At least the cat comes back.

177
00:17:54,784 --> 00:17:58,329
<i>Still pining for that two-timing slut?
There's a million women out there.</i>

178
00:17:58,496 --> 00:18:02,667
I don't want a million women.
I just want one.

179
00:18:02,959 --> 00:18:04,460
The perfect one.

180
00:18:04,627 --> 00:18:08,631
<i>- It don't exist, major.</i>
- Yeah. I know.

181
00:18:09,298 --> 00:18:11,300
<i>- What?</i>
- Just found a picture of you.

182
00:18:11,467 --> 00:18:12,927
<i>- How do I look?</i>
- Like shit.

183
00:18:13,094 --> 00:18:14,470
<i>Must be an old picture.</i>

184
00:18:14,637 --> 00:18:17,765
<i>Listen, bring me your hack
for a six-month overhaul.</i>

185
00:18:17,932 --> 00:18:19,350
- Negative.
<i>- ASAP.</i>

186
00:18:19,517 --> 00:18:20,768
I don't need one.

187
00:18:20,935 --> 00:18:24,981
<i>Hey, you forgetting who sat next to you
for 1000 missions? I know how you drive.</i>

188
00:18:25,148 --> 00:18:29,652
Finger, I drive a cab now,
not a space fighter.

189
00:18:29,819 --> 00:18:33,656
<i>Okay, so tell me. How many points
you got left on your license?</i>

190
00:18:33,823 --> 00:18:35,783
<i>Major, how many points?</i>

191
00:18:35,950 --> 00:18:37,368
At least 50.

192
00:18:37,535 --> 00:18:39,996
<i>You know what?
You gotta learn how to lie better.</i>

193
00:18:40,163 --> 00:18:41,372
<i>See you tonight.</i>

194
00:18:46,335 --> 00:18:48,671
<i>Welcome to paradise.</i>

195
00:18:48,838 --> 00:18:50,506
<i>Welcome to Fhloston Paradise.</i>

196
00:18:50,673 --> 00:18:53,676
<i>It's Ruby Rhod, your main man,
and I will tell you live at 5...</i>

197
00:18:53,843 --> 00:18:57,013
<i>...the winner of the super-green
Gemini Croquette Contest!</i>

198
00:18:57,180 --> 00:19:00,057
<i>The winner will go with me
for two days to Fhloston Paradise.</i>

199
00:19:00,224 --> 00:19:02,268
<i>So tune in to Radio Cosmos.</i>

200
00:19:02,435 --> 00:19:05,521
Don't watch it all day, sweetie.
It'll rot your brain.

201
00:19:05,688 --> 00:19:07,023
<i>For a perfect world.</i>

202
00:19:11,861 --> 00:19:14,030
- Give me the cash.
- Been here long?

203
00:19:14,197 --> 00:19:16,657
Yeah, long enough.
Come on, give me the cash.

204
00:19:16,824 --> 00:19:19,952
Is that a Z-140? Alleviated titanium.

205
00:19:20,119 --> 00:19:22,914
- Neurocharged assault model.
- Yeah. Yeah.

206
00:19:23,873 --> 00:19:26,167
Good thing for me it's not loaded.

207
00:19:27,084 --> 00:19:30,546
- What do you mean, it's not loaded?
- Well, you have to...

208
00:19:30,713 --> 00:19:32,965
...push that little yellow button
to load it.

209
00:19:36,928 --> 00:19:38,179
Take your time.

210
00:19:38,346 --> 00:19:40,264
Oh, God...

211
00:19:40,973 --> 00:19:42,642
You want me to--?

212
00:19:42,809 --> 00:19:44,227
Okay.

213
00:19:46,062 --> 00:19:47,396
There you go.

214
00:19:47,563 --> 00:19:49,565
Give me the cash!

215
00:19:55,738 --> 00:19:57,448
That's a very dangerous gun.

216
00:19:57,615 --> 00:20:01,244
Maybe you better let me
hang on to this one for you, huh?

217
00:20:01,828 --> 00:20:03,746
- You don't mind, do you? You sure?
- No.

218
00:20:03,913 --> 00:20:07,041
No. Take it. I don't need it.

219
00:20:12,547 --> 00:20:13,923
That's a very nice hat.

220
00:20:14,090 --> 00:20:15,883
You like it?

221
00:20:16,050 --> 00:20:17,635
God!

222
00:20:23,432 --> 00:20:25,142
<i>Please enter your license.</i>

223
00:20:25,309 --> 00:20:27,603
Yes. Yes, just a minute.

224
00:20:28,938 --> 00:20:31,440
<i>Welcome on board, Mr. Dallas.</i>

225
00:20:31,607 --> 00:20:34,318
Good morning. Sleep well? Me too.

226
00:20:34,902 --> 00:20:37,613
- I had a horrible nightmare.
<i>- Propulsion 2-X-4.</i>

227
00:20:41,909 --> 00:20:44,620
<i>You have five points left
on your license.</i>

228
00:20:44,787 --> 00:20:47,665
Yeah. Thank you for reminding me.

229
00:20:48,791 --> 00:20:51,210
<i>Have a nice day.</i>

230
00:20:51,711 --> 00:20:53,546
Why not?

231
00:21:01,470 --> 00:21:02,889
You have 48 hours.

232
00:21:03,055 --> 00:21:05,975
That's the time it needs to adapt
to our living conditions.

233
00:21:06,142 --> 00:21:08,144
- And then?
- And then it will be too late.

234
00:21:08,311 --> 00:21:12,148
The goal of this thing is not
to fight over money or power...

235
00:21:13,691 --> 00:21:16,861
...but to exterminate life.
All forms of life.

236
00:21:17,028 --> 00:21:20,072
So, what you're telling me,
there's nothing that can stop this.

237
00:21:20,823 --> 00:21:22,825
There is only one thing.

238
00:21:27,455 --> 00:21:31,125
<i>The Mondoshawan have in their
possession the weapon to defeat evil.</i>

239
00:21:31,292 --> 00:21:33,711
Four elements...

240
00:21:33,961 --> 00:21:36,172
...gathered around a fifth...

241
00:21:36,339 --> 00:21:40,843
...supreme being, the ultimate warrior,
created to protect life.

242
00:21:41,010 --> 00:21:44,388
Together, they produce what
the ancients call the Light of Creation.

243
00:21:44,555 --> 00:21:47,892
Able to bring life to the
farthest reaches of the universe.

244
00:21:48,059 --> 00:21:52,396
But if evil stands there...

245
00:21:54,023 --> 00:21:55,232
Then what?

246
00:21:55,399 --> 00:21:59,403
Then light turns to dark,
life to death...

247
00:21:59,570 --> 00:22:01,072
...forever.

248
00:22:03,074 --> 00:22:08,412
Sir, a Mondoshawan spaceship requests
permission to enter our territory.

249
00:22:09,080 --> 00:22:12,875
Give it permission to enter our
territory with our warmest regards.

250
00:22:13,042 --> 00:22:14,293
Thank you.

251
00:22:14,460 --> 00:22:16,671
<i>Permission to enter granted.</i>

252
00:22:33,062 --> 00:22:34,563
Showtime.

253
00:23:16,272 --> 00:23:18,107
We are lost.

254
00:23:18,941 --> 00:23:22,486
<i>Aknot, we are connected to Earth.</i>

255
00:23:25,281 --> 00:23:26,991
Mr. Zorg's office.

256
00:23:27,158 --> 00:23:28,409
<i>It's Aknot.</i>

257
00:23:28,576 --> 00:23:31,996
I'm so glad to hear you, Aknot.

258
00:23:32,288 --> 00:23:35,082
<i>The mission is accomplished.</i>

259
00:23:35,666 --> 00:23:39,253
<i>You'll have what you asked for
in a few hours.</i>

260
00:23:39,628 --> 00:23:42,089
Good. I'll meet you at my factory.

261
00:23:42,256 --> 00:23:44,717
The attack was launched
by two unregistered warships.

262
00:23:44,884 --> 00:23:47,511
Close all borders
and declare a state of general alert.

263
00:23:47,678 --> 00:23:50,598
Try to contact the Mondoshawans.
We owe them an explanation.

264
00:23:50,765 --> 00:23:54,560
Three hundred years of waiting,
for nothing.

265
00:23:54,935 --> 00:23:56,520
Father, go home and get some rest.

266
00:23:56,854 --> 00:23:58,355
No.

267
00:23:58,522 --> 00:24:00,524
The Mondoshawan...

268
00:24:00,733 --> 00:24:03,360
I am their contact on Earth.
They will come for me.

269
00:24:03,527 --> 00:24:06,363
This is government business now.
I will keep you informed.

270
00:24:09,283 --> 00:24:11,827
The rescue team has reported
from the crash site.

271
00:24:11,994 --> 00:24:13,370
Any survivors?

272
00:24:13,537 --> 00:24:14,872
Only one.

273
00:24:18,125 --> 00:24:19,668
Is that what you call a survivor?

274
00:24:19,835 --> 00:24:21,921
A few cells are still alive.
More than I need.

275
00:24:22,088 --> 00:24:25,132
- Have you identified it?
- The computer went off the charts.

276
00:24:25,299 --> 00:24:28,177
You see, normal human beings
have 40 DNA memo groups...

277
00:24:28,344 --> 00:24:30,888
...which is enough
for any species to perpetuate.

278
00:24:31,055 --> 00:24:34,016
This has 200,000 memo groups.

279
00:24:38,562 --> 00:24:43,234
- Sounds like a freak of nature to me.
- Yeah. Can't wait to meet him.

280
00:24:51,367 --> 00:24:52,701
You okay, general? Over here.

281
00:24:53,661 --> 00:24:55,579
Excuse me.

282
00:25:00,042 --> 00:25:02,503
Okay, general,
I wanna show you something here.

283
00:25:03,087 --> 00:25:05,881
This is a normal human DNA chain,
okay?

284
00:25:06,048 --> 00:25:08,217
You, me, anybody, right?

285
00:25:08,384 --> 00:25:09,718
Watch this.

286
00:25:10,761 --> 00:25:14,056
The compositional elements
of his DNA chain are the same as ours.

287
00:25:14,223 --> 00:25:17,434
There's simply more of them,
with infinite genetic knowledge.

288
00:25:17,601 --> 00:25:20,312
Almost like this being was engineered.

289
00:25:24,441 --> 00:25:25,818
- Is there any danger?
- No, no.

290
00:25:25,985 --> 00:25:28,863
We put it through the cellular
hygiene detector. The cell is...

291
00:25:29,029 --> 00:25:30,614
...for lack of a better word...

292
00:25:30,781 --> 00:25:32,533
...perfect.

293
00:25:33,492 --> 00:25:35,619
Okay. Go ahead.

294
00:25:35,786 --> 00:25:37,413
But Mr. Perfect better be polite.

295
00:25:37,580 --> 00:25:39,957
Otherwise, I turn him into cat food.

296
00:25:40,166 --> 00:25:41,417
Activate it.

297
00:26:12,948 --> 00:26:14,325
Tissue processing.

298
00:26:28,005 --> 00:26:31,133
Ten seconds to ultraviolet protection.

299
00:26:37,014 --> 00:26:40,643
The last phase. The cells are bombarded
by slightly greasy solar atoms...

300
00:26:40,809 --> 00:26:44,688
...which forces the body to react to
protect itself. That means growing skin.

301
00:26:44,855 --> 00:26:46,398
Wonderful.

302
00:26:51,737 --> 00:26:53,906
Reconstruction complete.

303
00:26:57,201 --> 00:26:59,286
Remove the shield.

304
00:27:07,253 --> 00:27:09,713
I told you. Perfect.

305
00:27:18,097 --> 00:27:19,431
Thermal bandages.

306
00:27:23,894 --> 00:27:28,232
I'd like to take a few pictures...

307
00:27:29,191 --> 00:27:30,567
...for the archives.

308
00:28:31,420 --> 00:28:34,465
- What's she saying?
- I don't know. Activate the phonic detector.

309
00:28:47,144 --> 00:28:49,313
Is--? Is that thing solid?

310
00:28:49,480 --> 00:28:50,898
- Unbreakable.
- Good.

311
00:29:01,116 --> 00:29:02,743
If you want out...

312
00:29:02,910 --> 00:29:06,622
...you're gonna have to learn to develop
those communication skills.

313
00:29:24,640 --> 00:29:26,016
General alert.

314
00:29:29,478 --> 00:29:31,188
Security.

315
00:29:52,751 --> 00:29:54,378
Perfect.

316
00:29:58,632 --> 00:30:00,884
Ladder on 18.

317
00:30:01,218 --> 00:30:03,846
- Two with me. The rest, main ventilation.
- Okay, sir.

318
00:30:23,073 --> 00:30:24,116
This way.

319
00:30:58,525 --> 00:31:01,445
Okay, lady. Stay calm.

320
00:31:01,612 --> 00:31:03,447
This is the police.

321
00:31:03,614 --> 00:31:05,407
There's nowhere else to go.

322
00:31:05,574 --> 00:31:09,578
You're gonna slowly turn around
and put your hands on the floor.

323
00:31:09,745 --> 00:31:11,330
Do you understand me?

324
00:31:15,042 --> 00:31:16,084
She doesn't.

325
00:31:40,943 --> 00:31:42,569
I think we need a flying unit here.

326
00:31:44,571 --> 00:31:46,031
<i>This is the police.</i>

327
00:31:46,198 --> 00:31:48,575
<i>This is the police.</i>

328
00:31:48,742 --> 00:31:50,702
We are processing your identification.

329
00:31:50,869 --> 00:31:53,372
<i>Please put your arms up
and follow our instructions.</i>

330
00:32:05,425 --> 00:32:06,718
She has no file.

331
00:32:15,894 --> 00:32:17,312
She dove off.

332
00:32:30,117 --> 00:32:31,785
- Sorry.
<i>- You just had an accident.</i>

333
00:32:31,952 --> 00:32:34,913
Yes. I know I just had an accident,
you daffy bastard.

334
00:32:36,498 --> 00:32:38,667
You have one point left
on your license. Yeah.

335
00:32:38,834 --> 00:32:40,335
Look out!

336
00:32:40,502 --> 00:32:42,296
Oh, no, left!

337
00:32:46,425 --> 00:32:48,343
I can't believe it. Shit.

338
00:32:54,224 --> 00:32:55,642
Any survivors?

339
00:33:01,523 --> 00:33:03,400
Hi.

340
00:33:06,445 --> 00:33:07,529
You okay?

341
00:33:35,265 --> 00:33:36,308
Boom.

342
00:33:36,475 --> 00:33:38,977
Boom. Yeah, I understand "boom."

343
00:33:39,853 --> 00:33:41,480
Bada boom.

344
00:33:42,064 --> 00:33:44,483
Big. Big bada boom.

345
00:33:44,650 --> 00:33:46,026
Big...

346
00:33:46,193 --> 00:33:47,736
...bada big boom.

347
00:33:47,903 --> 00:33:49,237
- Big boom.
- Yeah.

348
00:33:49,404 --> 00:33:52,115
- Yeah, big bada boom.
- Bada boom.

349
00:33:52,282 --> 00:33:54,701
Big boom. Big bada boom.

350
00:33:58,330 --> 00:34:00,791
You know,
you're lucky you're not dead.

351
00:34:03,210 --> 00:34:05,253
<i>This is a police control.</i>

352
00:34:05,587 --> 00:34:08,256
<i>Please keep your hands on the wheel.</i>

353
00:34:08,423 --> 00:34:11,426
<i>You have an unauthorized
passenger in your vehicle.</i>

354
00:34:11,593 --> 00:34:13,512
<i>We are going to arrest her.</i>

355
00:34:13,679 --> 00:34:15,347
Thank you for your cooperation.

356
00:34:15,514 --> 00:34:16,932
Sorry, honey.

357
00:34:17,099 --> 00:34:18,975
Looks like this is your ride.

358
00:34:19,142 --> 00:34:20,268
Open the door.

359
00:34:23,021 --> 00:34:24,356
I'm gonna do what they say.

360
00:34:26,525 --> 00:34:28,110
Sorry.

361
00:34:50,257 --> 00:34:52,551
"Please...

362
00:34:52,718 --> 00:34:54,720
...help."

363
00:34:54,886 --> 00:34:56,513
I only got one point on my license.

364
00:34:56,680 --> 00:35:00,475
I need that to get back to the garage
and get the cab a six-month overhaul.

365
00:35:00,642 --> 00:35:02,602
You understand.

366
00:35:03,895 --> 00:35:06,273
Can you please
open the passenger door?

367
00:35:08,275 --> 00:35:10,277
Please...

368
00:35:11,778 --> 00:35:13,822
...help.

369
00:35:15,365 --> 00:35:16,950
I can't.

370
00:35:21,663 --> 00:35:22,998
<i>I repeat...</i>

371
00:35:23,165 --> 00:35:25,250
...can you please open
your passenger door?

372
00:35:25,417 --> 00:35:27,669
Yeah. Yeah, sure.

373
00:35:27,836 --> 00:35:29,337
Why not?

374
00:35:43,351 --> 00:35:45,103
Thank you for your cooperation.

375
00:35:48,315 --> 00:35:49,608
Help.

376
00:35:51,109 --> 00:35:53,153
Finger's gonna kill me.

377
00:35:59,409 --> 00:36:00,619
Hey!

378
00:36:01,119 --> 00:36:02,704
Emergency! Emergency!

379
00:36:02,871 --> 00:36:04,581
<i>One point has been removed...</i>

380
00:36:04,748 --> 00:36:06,875
<i>- ...from your license.</i>
- Yes, I know!

381
00:36:07,042 --> 00:36:08,376
<i>from your license.</i>

382
00:36:12,047 --> 00:36:14,299
This is so stupid.

383
00:36:15,217 --> 00:36:17,511
<i>All units,
assist in pursuit of yellow cab.</i>

384
00:36:17,677 --> 00:36:19,596
Unit 47, we're on the way...

385
00:36:19,763 --> 00:36:21,139
...as soon as we finish lunch.

386
00:36:24,142 --> 00:36:26,978
- Two golden menus.
- Thank you.

387
00:36:27,145 --> 00:36:31,858
I'm too old, too tired and too hungry
to go chasing some hot rod.

388
00:36:33,735 --> 00:36:35,237
Thank you so much.

389
00:36:38,865 --> 00:36:41,409
And I'm definitely too thirsty.

390
00:36:41,576 --> 00:36:43,745
Look out!

391
00:36:47,749 --> 00:36:49,793
We got lucky.

392
00:36:50,502 --> 00:36:53,213
If they don't chase you after a mile,
they don't chase you.

393
00:37:00,720 --> 00:37:02,597
Maybe it's two miles.

394
00:37:03,181 --> 00:37:04,599
Hang on.

395
00:37:13,400 --> 00:37:16,945
Look, lady, I only speak two languages:
English and bad English!

396
00:37:19,406 --> 00:37:20,407
Run an ID.

397
00:37:23,118 --> 00:37:25,287
Don't get me wrong,
I'm all for conversation...

398
00:37:25,453 --> 00:37:27,998
...but maybe you can just
shut up for a minute!

399
00:37:29,791 --> 00:37:33,545
- He's got a scan blocker.
- Means he's a car thief. Blast him.

400
00:37:37,924 --> 00:37:40,385
I don't know what you did
to piss these guys off...

401
00:37:41,928 --> 00:37:44,431
...but they are really pissed off!
Hold on!

402
00:38:01,948 --> 00:38:03,742
I think we're safe for a while.

403
00:38:28,558 --> 00:38:31,144
You wanna play it soft?
I'll play it soft.

404
00:38:31,311 --> 00:38:34,689
You wanna play it hard?
Let's play it hard.

405
00:38:45,116 --> 00:38:47,494
If I can get to the fog,
we'll be all right.

406
00:38:50,038 --> 00:38:51,957
If we make the fog.

407
00:39:09,641 --> 00:39:12,560
How do they expect us
to find anything in this shit?

408
00:39:18,149 --> 00:39:22,153
We're just gonna wait here until
things quiet down, if you don't mind.

409
00:39:23,238 --> 00:39:24,531
Hey.

410
00:39:36,042 --> 00:39:37,627
Shit.

411
00:39:46,553 --> 00:39:48,304
You okay?

412
00:39:49,848 --> 00:39:51,099
Priest.

413
00:39:51,599 --> 00:39:53,893
You don't need a priest,
you just need a doctor.

414
00:39:54,310 --> 00:39:58,565
- Vito Cornelius.
- What?

415
00:39:58,773 --> 00:40:00,734
Priest.

416
00:40:03,695 --> 00:40:04,779
Yes?

417
00:40:05,280 --> 00:40:07,574
I'm looking for a priest.

418
00:40:07,741 --> 00:40:10,452
The weddings are one floor down,
my son. Congratulations.

419
00:40:13,079 --> 00:40:15,248
She's not my bride. She's my fare.

420
00:40:15,415 --> 00:40:18,960
She's looking for Vito Cornelius.
The phone book said he lived here.

421
00:40:19,127 --> 00:40:22,172
Yes, that's me,
but I don't know who she is.

422
00:40:22,338 --> 00:40:24,966
Nobody knows who she is.
No file, no ID, nothing.

423
00:40:25,133 --> 00:40:27,177
She's got a tattoo on this arm, here.

424
00:40:28,303 --> 00:40:30,013
Tattoo?

425
00:40:39,939 --> 00:40:41,649
Fifth...

426
00:40:41,816 --> 00:40:43,651
...element.

427
00:40:48,656 --> 00:40:50,325
Finger's gonna kill me.

428
00:40:50,492 --> 00:40:53,119
- Hey! Wake up.
- Who are you?

429
00:40:53,286 --> 00:40:55,663
I brought the girl, remember?
The redhead.

430
00:40:57,874 --> 00:41:00,960
She just dropped in on me.
Started speaking this bizarre language.

431
00:41:01,127 --> 00:41:04,422
It's not bizarre.
It's the divine language.

432
00:41:04,589 --> 00:41:06,341
- The ancient language.
- Okay.

433
00:41:06,508 --> 00:41:09,761
Spoken throughout the universe
before time was time.

434
00:41:11,846 --> 00:41:13,973
- He's a she.
- You noticed that, huh?

435
00:41:14,724 --> 00:41:16,476
Yes.

436
00:41:21,523 --> 00:41:23,858
- It's a miracle.
- Miracle she's not dead.

437
00:41:24,025 --> 00:41:25,693
Not a moment to lose. Wake her up.

438
00:41:25,860 --> 00:41:30,281
But gently, because this woman is
mankind's most precious possession.

439
00:41:30,448 --> 00:41:33,535
She-- She is perfect.

440
00:41:37,664 --> 00:41:39,582
Perfect.

441
00:41:46,089 --> 00:41:47,382
More dignified.

442
00:41:47,549 --> 00:41:49,384
Hey, lady.

443
00:41:49,551 --> 00:41:51,261
Wake up.

444
00:42:02,105 --> 00:42:04,607
You're right. You're right.
I shouldn't have done that.

445
00:42:04,774 --> 00:42:06,234
I-- It was wrong to kiss you.

446
00:42:06,401 --> 00:42:08,027
He said to wake you gently.

447
00:42:08,194 --> 00:42:09,612
You're right. You're right.

448
00:42:12,198 --> 00:42:15,451
Just thought you might
remember me from the cab.

449
00:42:15,618 --> 00:42:16,828
Remember?

450
00:42:16,995 --> 00:42:18,079
"Bada boom"?

451
00:42:19,122 --> 00:42:20,832
- "Big bada boom"?
- Boom?

452
00:42:21,124 --> 00:42:23,793
Boom. Big bada boom.
In the cab. Here, look.

453
00:42:23,960 --> 00:42:26,462
I drive a cab. This is me.

454
00:42:26,629 --> 00:42:28,673
Korben Dallas.

455
00:42:29,132 --> 00:42:30,550
Korben. You understand?

456
00:42:31,134 --> 00:42:33,303
Here. Take it, go ahead.

457
00:42:34,345 --> 00:42:37,265
You can call me when you learn
how to speak English.

458
00:42:39,809 --> 00:42:41,269
Just kidding. Kidding.

459
00:42:43,771 --> 00:42:45,273
And you--? What is your name?

460
00:42:46,608 --> 00:42:47,984
You.

461
00:42:48,151 --> 00:42:50,069
Korben.

462
00:42:52,155 --> 00:42:55,325
Leeloo Minai Lekarariba-Laminai-Tchai
Ekbat De Sebat.

463
00:42:56,326 --> 00:42:58,494
Good. That's--

464
00:42:58,661 --> 00:43:00,455
That whole thing's your name, huh?

465
00:43:01,664 --> 00:43:03,291
Do you have...

466
00:43:04,500 --> 00:43:05,668
...a shorter name?

467
00:43:08,713 --> 00:43:10,423
Short.

468
00:43:12,133 --> 00:43:13,343
Korben Dallas.

469
00:43:16,512 --> 00:43:17,805
Leeloo.

470
00:43:19,974 --> 00:43:21,142
Leeloo.

471
00:43:22,185 --> 00:43:23,645
Korben, Leeloo.

472
00:43:24,020 --> 00:43:26,105
Leeloo, Korben.

473
00:43:43,456 --> 00:43:47,210
- Father, you sure she's a supreme being?
- Absolutely sure.

474
00:43:47,377 --> 00:43:49,379
Old friends. Okay.

475
00:43:49,545 --> 00:43:51,547
Yeah. You're right. Okay.

476
00:43:51,756 --> 00:43:54,300
- Ask her for my gun back please.
- What's your name?

477
00:43:54,550 --> 00:43:56,636
Korben Dallas.

478
00:43:56,928 --> 00:43:58,888
Thank you, Mr. Dallas,
for all your help.

479
00:43:59,055 --> 00:44:02,058
Thank you. You've been so kind,
but now the girl needs some rest.

480
00:44:02,225 --> 00:44:04,018
Because she's been on a long trip.

481
00:44:04,185 --> 00:44:07,146
Yes. I know.
I was there when she landed.

482
00:44:07,313 --> 00:44:08,940
Wait, wait. Hey, wait, Father.

483
00:44:09,107 --> 00:44:12,944
She said something I didn't understand.
Well, I didn't understand any of it.

484
00:44:13,111 --> 00:44:16,531
- What does "ekto gamat" mean?
- "Never without my permission."

485
00:44:17,198 --> 00:44:18,908
- That's what I thought.
- Yeah.

486
00:44:27,083 --> 00:44:29,294
I shouldn't have kissed her.

487
00:44:34,215 --> 00:44:38,928
Oh, no. I'm so sorry.
I forgot your food.

488
00:44:39,554 --> 00:44:41,889
How about some nice Thai food
to apologize, huh?

489
00:44:42,056 --> 00:44:44,058
Yeah. Yeah, hold on. What?

490
00:44:44,225 --> 00:44:46,769
<i>Hey, buddy, I'm waiting all day here.</i>

491
00:44:46,936 --> 00:44:48,563
- Finger.
<i>- Where is the cab?</i>

492
00:44:48,730 --> 00:44:52,567
- Car's running fine. Purring like a kitten.
<i>- Fine. What "fine"?</i>

493
00:44:52,734 --> 00:44:55,570
<i>I know you, Dallas.
"Fine" ain't in your vocabulary.</i>

494
00:44:55,737 --> 00:44:57,989
<i>You can tell your old buddy Finger
what happened.</i>

495
00:44:58,156 --> 00:45:00,241
<i>- What? You save the planet?</i>
- Listen--

496
00:45:00,408 --> 00:45:03,536
<i>You dinged the fender again. Right?
Dinged the goddamn fender again.</i>

497
00:45:03,703 --> 00:45:08,082
Finger, I was on my way over to see you,
and a big fare fell in my lap.

498
00:45:08,249 --> 00:45:11,794
You know, one of these really big fares
that you just can't resist.

499
00:45:12,128 --> 00:45:14,088
<i>How big?</i>

500
00:45:21,929 --> 00:45:23,765
Five-nine...

501
00:45:24,307 --> 00:45:25,600
...blue eyes...

502
00:45:25,767 --> 00:45:27,935
...long legs, great skin.

503
00:45:28,102 --> 00:45:30,480
You know, perfect.

504
00:45:30,646 --> 00:45:31,647
<i>I see.</i>

505
00:45:31,814 --> 00:45:36,110
<i>And this perfect fare, she got a name?</i>

506
00:45:36,277 --> 00:45:39,822
Yeah. Leeloo.

507
00:45:46,829 --> 00:45:48,122
What's she doing?

508
00:45:48,289 --> 00:45:51,292
Learning our history,
the last 5000 years that she's missed.

509
00:45:51,459 --> 00:45:53,836
She's been asleep for quite a while,
you know.

510
00:46:05,348 --> 00:46:08,768
Father, I know she's been through a lot,
but we don't have much time.

511
00:46:08,935 --> 00:46:10,728
Yes. You're right.

512
00:46:12,313 --> 00:46:13,689
Chicken.

513
00:46:13,856 --> 00:46:15,441
Good.

514
00:46:18,528 --> 00:46:20,405
Chicken.

515
00:46:24,784 --> 00:46:26,953
I'm really sorry to interrupt you...

516
00:46:27,120 --> 00:46:30,039
...but the case...

517
00:46:30,206 --> 00:46:32,166
...with the stones...

518
00:46:33,042 --> 00:46:34,043
...where is it?

519
00:46:36,421 --> 00:46:37,672
Stolen?

520
00:46:40,258 --> 00:46:43,386
Who in God's name
would do such a thing?

521
00:46:47,932 --> 00:46:51,102
Excuse me, sir. The council is worried
about the economy heating up.

522
00:46:51,269 --> 00:46:53,813
They wondered if it could
be possible to fire 500,000?

523
00:46:53,980 --> 00:46:57,024
I thought from one of the smaller
companies no one would notice.

524
00:46:57,191 --> 00:46:59,819
- Like one of the cab companies.
- Fire one million.

525
00:46:59,986 --> 00:47:03,823
But 500,000...

526
00:47:07,535 --> 00:47:10,371
One million. Fine, sir.

527
00:47:10,538 --> 00:47:12,248
Sorry to have disturbed you.

528
00:47:21,841 --> 00:47:23,176
Oh, it's...

529
00:47:23,342 --> 00:47:25,428
- It's for the Supreme...
- Yes, yes, yes.

530
00:47:27,054 --> 00:47:28,723
Oh, sorry.

531
00:47:29,557 --> 00:47:33,102
I didn't know your size,
and I found you this makeup box.

532
00:47:33,269 --> 00:47:35,980
Okay? You just put it like that.

533
00:47:37,398 --> 00:47:40,067
Yes, there was a man with a limp...

534
00:47:40,276 --> 00:47:43,362
...who came here a month ago
asking questions about the stones.

535
00:47:43,529 --> 00:47:45,031
He said he was an art dealer.

536
00:47:48,117 --> 00:47:50,411
What was his name?

537
00:47:52,455 --> 00:47:54,707
I'm so bad with names.

538
00:47:59,754 --> 00:48:03,216
- They really make her--
- Perfect. I know.

539
00:48:07,553 --> 00:48:09,055
What did she say?

540
00:48:10,765 --> 00:48:13,601
<i>She says she knows
exactly where they are.</i>

541
00:48:16,771 --> 00:48:20,983
My dear Aknot, how about those
two little planes that you borrowed?

542
00:48:21,484 --> 00:48:24,612
Aknot, is that you?
What an ugly face.

543
00:48:24,779 --> 00:48:26,572
It doesn't suit you.

544
00:48:26,864 --> 00:48:28,741
Take it off.

545
00:48:30,785 --> 00:48:31,953
That's better.

546
00:48:32,119 --> 00:48:33,955
Never be ashamed of who you are.

547
00:48:34,121 --> 00:48:35,831
You're warriors. Be proud.

548
00:48:35,998 --> 00:48:39,126
So what if the federal government
scattered your people to the wind.

549
00:48:39,335 --> 00:48:42,421
What doesn't kill you
makes you stronger.

550
00:48:42,588 --> 00:48:45,466
Your time for revenge is at hand.

551
00:48:45,675 --> 00:48:48,594
Voilà: the ZF-1.

552
00:48:50,763 --> 00:48:54,183
It's light. Handle's adjustable for easy
carrying. Good for righties and lefties.

553
00:48:54,350 --> 00:48:58,813
Breaks down into four parts, undetectable
by x-ray. Ideal for discreet interventions.

554
00:48:58,980 --> 00:49:00,147
A word on firepower:

555
00:49:00,314 --> 00:49:03,818
Titanium recharger, 3000-round clip
with bursts of three to 300.

556
00:49:03,985 --> 00:49:07,697
With the replay button, another
Zorg invention, it's even easier.

557
00:49:07,989 --> 00:49:09,156
One shot...

558
00:49:10,157 --> 00:49:13,411
...and replay sends every
following shot to the same location.

559
00:49:19,917 --> 00:49:23,337
And to finish the job,
all the Zorg oldies but goldies.

560
00:49:24,130 --> 00:49:25,172
Rocket launcher.

561
00:49:27,341 --> 00:49:30,511
Arrow launcher with exploding
or poisonous-gas heads.

562
00:49:31,929 --> 00:49:34,056
Very practical.
Our famous net launcher.

563
00:49:36,017 --> 00:49:38,227
The always-efficient flamethrower.

564
00:49:41,897 --> 00:49:42,940
My favorite.

565
00:49:43,524 --> 00:49:47,987
And for the grand finale,
the all-new ice-cube system.

566
00:49:56,621 --> 00:50:00,041
Four full crates
delivered right on time.

567
00:50:01,042 --> 00:50:04,879
And what about you, my dear Aknot?
Did you bring me what I asked you for?

568
00:50:06,213 --> 00:50:08,132
Yes.

569
00:50:13,179 --> 00:50:15,264
Magnificent.

570
00:50:19,185 --> 00:50:20,603
This--

571
00:50:21,896 --> 00:50:24,065
This case is empty.

572
00:50:25,733 --> 00:50:27,902
- What do you mean, empty?
- Empty...

573
00:50:28,069 --> 00:50:30,071
...the opposite of full.

574
00:50:30,237 --> 00:50:34,283
This case is supposed to be full!

575
00:50:35,910 --> 00:50:37,411
Anyone care to explain?

576
00:50:39,664 --> 00:50:43,959
The Guardians gave the stones
to someone that they could trust.

577
00:50:46,921 --> 00:50:48,923
Who took another route.

578
00:50:50,508 --> 00:50:53,135
She's supposed
to contact this person...

579
00:50:53,302 --> 00:50:54,929
...in a hotel.

580
00:50:59,100 --> 00:51:00,976
And she's looking for the address.

581
00:51:01,143 --> 00:51:02,436
Easy.

582
00:51:04,063 --> 00:51:05,856
Dot.

583
00:51:09,652 --> 00:51:12,488
It's Planet Fhloston
in the Angel Constellation.

584
00:51:14,448 --> 00:51:17,034
- We're saved.
- I'm screwed.

585
00:51:17,201 --> 00:51:19,453
You asked for a case.
We brought you a case.

586
00:51:19,620 --> 00:51:22,123
A case with four stones in it!

587
00:51:22,289 --> 00:51:24,625
Not one or two or three, but four!

588
00:51:24,792 --> 00:51:25,960
Four stones!

589
00:51:26,127 --> 00:51:28,963
What the hell am I supposed to do
with an empty case?

590
00:51:29,130 --> 00:51:31,298
We are warriors, not merchants.

591
00:51:31,465 --> 00:51:34,593
But you can still count!
Look, it's easy. Look at my fingers.

592
00:51:34,760 --> 00:51:36,595
Four stones, four crates.

593
00:51:36,762 --> 00:51:41,642
Zero stones, zero crates!
Pack everything up! We're out of here!

594
00:51:44,979 --> 00:51:47,022
We risked our lives.

595
00:51:47,189 --> 00:51:51,110
I believe a little compensation
is in order.

596
00:51:52,653 --> 00:51:55,781
So you are merchants after all.

597
00:51:56,866 --> 00:51:58,868
Leave them one crate...

598
00:51:59,034 --> 00:52:01,120
...for the cause.

599
00:52:02,496 --> 00:52:05,249
I don't like warriors.
Too narrow-minded, no subtlety...

600
00:52:05,416 --> 00:52:08,669
...and worse, they fight
for hopeless causes, honor.

601
00:52:08,836 --> 00:52:11,672
Honor's killed millions of people.
Hasn't saved a single one.

602
00:52:11,839 --> 00:52:14,341
I'll tell you what I do like though,
a killer.

603
00:52:14,508 --> 00:52:17,928
A dyed-in-the-wool killer, cold-blooded,
clean, methodical and thorough.

604
00:52:18,095 --> 00:52:20,264
Now,
a real killer picking up the ZF-1...

605
00:52:20,431 --> 00:52:23,768
...would've asked about the red button
on the bottom of the gun.

606
00:52:42,244 --> 00:52:43,621
Bring me the priest.

607
00:52:46,207 --> 00:52:48,918
I got everything we need
to know about Fhloston Paradise...

608
00:52:49,084 --> 00:52:50,586
...and a blueprint of the hotel.

609
00:52:50,753 --> 00:52:53,839
Good work. Now, all we've gotta do
is find a way of getting there.

610
00:52:54,006 --> 00:52:56,467
Not gonna be easy.
There's a charity ball tomorrow.

611
00:52:56,634 --> 00:53:00,054
Flights are full, and with all the
celebrities, the hotel will be guarded.

612
00:53:00,221 --> 00:53:02,431
But there must be a way
of getting there.

613
00:53:08,103 --> 00:53:09,396
I'll get it.

614
00:53:11,232 --> 00:53:12,775
Weddings?

615
00:53:14,735 --> 00:53:15,820
Not really.

616
00:53:15,986 --> 00:53:18,823
- Mr. Zorg would like to talk to you.
- Mister who?

617
00:53:18,989 --> 00:53:20,574
Mr. Zorg.

618
00:53:21,242 --> 00:53:23,536
Jean-Baptiste Emmanuel...

619
00:53:23,702 --> 00:53:24,703
...Zorg.

620
00:53:28,415 --> 00:53:30,543
It's nice to see you again, Father.

621
00:53:30,709 --> 00:53:33,462
I remember you now.

622
00:53:33,629 --> 00:53:36,173
The so-called art dealer.

623
00:53:36,340 --> 00:53:40,386
Well, I'm glad you got your memory back
because you're gonna need it.

624
00:53:42,555 --> 00:53:43,973
Where are the stones?

625
00:53:44,723 --> 00:53:48,143
I don't know. And even if I did,
I wouldn't tell somebody like you.

626
00:53:48,310 --> 00:53:49,770
Why?

627
00:53:50,229 --> 00:53:54,108
- What's wrong with me?
- I try to serve life.

628
00:53:54,942 --> 00:53:56,735
But you only...

629
00:53:56,902 --> 00:53:58,320
...seem to want to destroy it.

630
00:53:59,113 --> 00:54:01,073
Oh, Father...

631
00:54:01,615 --> 00:54:03,409
...you're so wrong.

632
00:54:03,576 --> 00:54:04,702
Let me explain.

633
00:54:08,831 --> 00:54:10,833
Life, which you so nobly serve...

634
00:54:11,000 --> 00:54:13,711
...comes from destruction,
disorder and chaos.

635
00:54:13,878 --> 00:54:15,337
Now, take this empty glass.

636
00:54:15,504 --> 00:54:18,465
Here it is, peaceful, serene, boring.

637
00:54:18,632 --> 00:54:20,467
But if it is...

638
00:54:21,343 --> 00:54:22,636
...destroyed...

639
00:54:26,807 --> 00:54:29,268
Look at all these little things.
So busy now.

640
00:54:29,435 --> 00:54:31,729
Notice how each one is useful.

641
00:54:34,607 --> 00:54:38,485
What a lovely ballet ensues,
so full of form and color.

642
00:54:38,652 --> 00:54:42,364
Now, think about all those people
that created them.

643
00:54:42,573 --> 00:54:46,660
Technicians, engineers. People who will
be able to feed their children tonight...

644
00:54:46,827 --> 00:54:50,789
...so those children can grow up big and
strong, and have children of their own...

645
00:54:50,956 --> 00:54:52,249
...and so on and so forth.

646
00:54:52,416 --> 00:54:55,753
Thus adding to the great chain...

647
00:54:55,961 --> 00:54:57,463
...of life.

648
00:55:00,007 --> 00:55:01,675
<i>Water. Fruit.</i>

649
00:55:01,842 --> 00:55:04,595
You see, Father,
by creating a little destruction...

650
00:55:04,762 --> 00:55:05,846
<i>A cherry.</i>

651
00:55:06,013 --> 00:55:07,806
...I'm, in fact, encouraging life.

652
00:55:08,349 --> 00:55:11,185
In reality, you and I
are in the same business.

653
00:55:12,186 --> 00:55:13,228
Cheers.

654
00:55:30,371 --> 00:55:32,539
Where's the robot
to pat you on the back?

655
00:55:34,583 --> 00:55:36,001
Or the engineer?

656
00:55:40,756 --> 00:55:43,384
Or their children, maybe?

657
00:55:52,184 --> 00:55:54,812
There, you see now
how all your so-called power...

658
00:55:54,979 --> 00:55:57,106
...counts for absolutely nothing?

659
00:55:57,272 --> 00:56:01,735
How your entire empire
of destruction comes crashing down...

660
00:56:01,902 --> 00:56:06,073
...all because of one little cherry.

661
00:56:19,420 --> 00:56:21,046
You saved my life...

662
00:56:21,213 --> 00:56:23,757
...and in return, I'll spare yours...

663
00:56:24,049 --> 00:56:25,676
...for now.

664
00:56:25,926 --> 00:56:27,219
You're a monster, Zorg.

665
00:56:29,263 --> 00:56:30,848
I know.

666
00:56:34,685 --> 00:56:37,104
Torture who you have to,
the president, I don't care.

667
00:56:37,271 --> 00:56:39,773
Just bring me those stones.

668
00:56:39,940 --> 00:56:41,775
You have one hour.

669
00:56:56,457 --> 00:56:59,418
It's gobbling up all the communication
satellites in the galaxy.

670
00:56:59,626 --> 00:57:02,296
Why in the hell
is it eating up all the satellites?

671
00:57:02,463 --> 00:57:04,923
We're working on it, Mr. President.

672
00:57:15,976 --> 00:57:17,644
I managed to contact the Mondoshawan.

673
00:57:17,811 --> 00:57:20,147
They deplore the incident
but accept our apologies.

674
00:57:20,314 --> 00:57:22,483
And the stones? Did you find them?

675
00:57:22,649 --> 00:57:24,985
- The stones weren't aboard the ship.
- What?

676
00:57:25,152 --> 00:57:28,155
The Mondoshawan never
fully trusted the human race.

677
00:57:28,322 --> 00:57:30,783
<i>So they gave up the stones
to someone they do trust.</i>

678
00:57:30,991 --> 00:57:33,994
<i>Her name is Plavalaguna.
She's a diva.</i>

679
00:57:34,161 --> 00:57:37,706
She's singing at a charity ball
in Fhloston Paradise in a few hours.

680
00:57:37,873 --> 00:57:39,374
She has the stones with her.

681
00:57:39,541 --> 00:57:41,919
The Mondoshawans have--

682
00:57:42,086 --> 00:57:45,255
All we have to do is send someone
to get the stones, bring them back.

683
00:57:45,422 --> 00:57:46,507
Excellent.

684
00:57:49,301 --> 00:57:51,845
I want this operation to be
discreet as possible.

685
00:57:52,012 --> 00:57:54,181
No troops. No big operation.

686
00:57:54,848 --> 00:57:56,850
I want your best man to go undercover.

687
00:57:57,017 --> 00:57:58,811
I have the perfect one.

688
00:58:02,856 --> 00:58:05,109
- You got a message.
- Yeah.

689
00:58:05,275 --> 00:58:06,985
Not gonna open it?
Could be important.

690
00:58:07,152 --> 00:58:10,823
Yeah. Like the last two I got
were important.

691
00:58:10,989 --> 00:58:14,493
First one was from my wife
telling me she's leaving.

692
00:58:14,660 --> 00:58:18,413
The second was from my lawyer
telling me he was leaving with my wife.

693
00:58:19,039 --> 00:58:20,374
That is bad luck.

694
00:58:20,541 --> 00:58:21,875
But grandfather say:

695
00:58:22,042 --> 00:58:25,504
"It never rain every day."
This is good news, guaranteed.

696
00:58:26,672 --> 00:58:27,714
I bet you lunch.

697
00:58:28,882 --> 00:58:30,509
Okay.

698
00:58:33,220 --> 00:58:34,847
Come on.

699
00:58:36,890 --> 00:58:38,058
"You are fired."

700
00:58:39,476 --> 00:58:42,604
Oh, I'm-- I'm sorry.

701
00:58:45,149 --> 00:58:46,233
Well...

702
00:58:47,442 --> 00:58:48,819
...at least I won lunch.

703
00:58:48,986 --> 00:58:53,282
Good philosophy.
See good in bad. I like. Yeah.

704
00:58:53,448 --> 00:58:55,367
- Hello.
<i>- Korben, sweetheart.</i>

705
00:58:55,534 --> 00:58:57,828
<i>You got broken fingers?
You can't punch my number?</i>

706
00:58:57,995 --> 00:58:59,913
- Hi, Mom.
<i>- Seventeen messages.</i>

707
00:59:00,080 --> 00:59:03,709
<i>And don't tell me your machine is
broken again. They last 1000 years.</i>

708
00:59:03,876 --> 00:59:07,254
Mr. Kim, you should go.
This is gonna take a minute.

709
00:59:07,421 --> 00:59:10,299
<i>You don't feed your cat a croquette,
who you love more than me.</i>

710
00:59:10,465 --> 00:59:13,886
<i>- She didn't breast-feed you. I did.</i>
- Goodbye, Mr. Dallas.

711
00:59:14,845 --> 00:59:15,971
Good fortune for you.

712
00:59:16,138 --> 00:59:19,141
<i>You don't have a girl.
Oh, Christ, I'll never be a grandmother.</i>

713
00:59:19,308 --> 00:59:21,894
- It bring you good luck!
- Yeah. Sure.

714
00:59:28,609 --> 00:59:31,486
<i>Korben, my body's failing me.
You have to take me on this trip.</i>

715
00:59:31,653 --> 00:59:34,907
- Ma, what are you talking about?
<i>- You wanna make your mother beg?</i>

716
00:59:35,073 --> 00:59:38,827
I don't wanna make you beg. All I want
is an explanation. Look, I just got in.

717
00:59:38,994 --> 00:59:41,788
I just smashed my cab.
I lost my job. I got mugged.

718
00:59:41,955 --> 00:59:45,500
Besides that, everything's peachy.
Thanks for asking.

719
00:59:45,667 --> 00:59:48,587
Now, will you just settle down
and explain this to me calmly?

720
00:59:48,754 --> 00:59:53,634
<i>So you don't know you won a trip to
Fhloston Paradise for two for 10 days?</i>

721
00:59:53,800 --> 00:59:58,305
<i>And I suppose you're gonna leave me on
the lunar surface to freeze my ass off.</i>

722
00:59:58,472 --> 01:00:00,766
If I'd won a trip, I'd know about it.

723
01:00:00,933 --> 01:00:02,809
Somebody would've notified me.

724
01:00:04,603 --> 01:00:08,690
<i>They've been blaring your name out on
the radio for the last hour, you big ape.</i>

725
01:00:12,903 --> 01:00:13,987
Ma, I'll call you back.

726
01:00:17,658 --> 01:00:20,911
General Munro, how nice to see you
in the 5000 block.

727
01:00:22,788 --> 01:00:24,706
Nice apartment, major.

728
01:00:24,873 --> 01:00:28,585
Looks like you settled into a wonderful
life. Heard you lost your job.

729
01:00:29,586 --> 01:00:31,797
You heard that, huh?

730
01:00:32,339 --> 01:00:34,800
Well, don't worry. I'll get another job.

731
01:00:34,967 --> 01:00:36,969
Don't bother. We have one for you.

732
01:00:37,678 --> 01:00:40,347
"Major Dallas, you've been
selected for a mission."

733
01:00:40,514 --> 01:00:42,599
- What mission?
- To save the world.

734
01:00:43,517 --> 01:00:45,310
"You leave for Fhloston Paradise.

735
01:00:45,477 --> 01:00:49,273
Retrieve four stones from the diva
Plavalaguna and bring them back."

736
01:00:49,439 --> 01:00:52,067
- Any questions?
- Yeah. Just one. Why me?

737
01:00:52,234 --> 01:00:55,654
- I retired six months ago, you remember?
- Three reasons.

738
01:00:55,821 --> 01:00:59,616
One, as a member of the Elite
Special Forces Unit of the army...

739
01:00:59,783 --> 01:01:03,370
...you are an expert in the use of
all necessary weapons and spacecraft.

740
01:01:03,870 --> 01:01:07,040
Two, you're the most highly
decorated member of your unit.

741
01:01:07,207 --> 01:01:09,418
- The third?
- Of all the members of your unit...

742
01:01:09,584 --> 01:01:11,586
...you're the only one left alive.

743
01:01:12,296 --> 01:01:14,881
- You check your messages?
- I've had enough good news.

744
01:01:15,048 --> 01:01:16,550
Might be important.

745
01:01:19,344 --> 01:01:20,387
<i>You're a winner!</i>

746
01:01:20,554 --> 01:01:24,641
You've won the annual Gemini Contest
and a trip to Fhloston Paradise for two.

747
01:01:27,060 --> 01:01:28,603
Here are your tickets.

748
01:01:28,770 --> 01:01:30,772
You rigged the contest?

749
01:01:30,939 --> 01:01:32,816
Congratulations.

750
01:01:34,985 --> 01:01:39,114
- Couldn't think of anything more discreet?
- Old tricks are the best tricks.

751
01:01:39,281 --> 01:01:41,992
Major Iceborg will
accompany you as your wife.

752
01:01:45,162 --> 01:01:46,371
I am not going.

753
01:01:47,789 --> 01:01:48,874
Why not?

754
01:02:00,010 --> 01:02:02,012
Excuse me, general.

755
01:02:03,680 --> 01:02:05,932
Who is it? Who is it?

756
01:02:08,769 --> 01:02:10,354
- My wife.
- You remarried?

757
01:02:10,520 --> 01:02:13,440
Yes. No. I just met this girl,
but I'm gonna marry her.

758
01:02:13,607 --> 01:02:17,611
I love her, but she hates the military. She
knows the military ruined my last marriage.

759
01:02:17,778 --> 01:02:20,572
Wants nothing to do with it.
If she sees you, she'll kill me.

760
01:02:20,739 --> 01:02:22,366
- Major--
- You gotta hide somewhere.

761
01:02:22,532 --> 01:02:26,286
- You gotta help me. Hide somewhere.
- We'd love to, but where can we hide?

762
01:02:30,457 --> 01:02:33,627
- Major, we don't have time for this.
- It's just for one minute.

763
01:02:33,794 --> 01:02:35,796
You have no idea
how much you're helping me.

764
01:02:35,962 --> 01:02:38,048
No idea. You have no idea.

765
01:02:38,215 --> 01:02:40,550
- I'm going to be happily married.
- Major! Major!

766
01:02:40,717 --> 01:02:43,428
- The three of us won't fit in there.
- Sure you will.

767
01:02:45,055 --> 01:02:46,807
Major!

768
01:02:47,182 --> 01:02:48,475
You're on my foot.

769
01:02:48,642 --> 01:02:50,519
Major! Major!

770
01:02:55,315 --> 01:02:56,650
Hi.

771
01:02:57,150 --> 01:02:59,861
I'm really sorry to resort to this,
Mr. Wallace--

772
01:03:00,028 --> 01:03:01,655
- Dallas.
- Dallas.

773
01:03:01,822 --> 01:03:05,033
We heard about your good luck
and need your tickets for Fhloston.

774
01:03:05,200 --> 01:03:07,202
This the way priests
usually take vacations?

775
01:03:07,369 --> 01:03:10,414
- Not vacation. We're on a mission.
- What kind of mission?

776
01:03:11,164 --> 01:03:13,250
We have to save the world, my son.

777
01:03:15,127 --> 01:03:18,255
- You're gonna save the world?
- Yes.

778
01:03:21,925 --> 01:03:23,969
Down there. Down there.

779
01:03:24,177 --> 01:03:25,804
Yeah. Come with me.

780
01:03:31,768 --> 01:03:34,354
<i>This is a police control.</i>

781
01:03:34,521 --> 01:03:37,649
<i>This is not an exercise.</i>

782
01:03:39,526 --> 01:03:42,404
Come on, get in here.
For one minute, all right?

783
01:03:42,571 --> 01:03:43,989
Just one minute. I promise.

784
01:03:44,156 --> 01:03:47,117
<i>- This is a police control.</i>
- Don't touch anything.

785
01:03:47,284 --> 01:03:49,828
<i>This is not an exercise.</i>

786
01:03:49,995 --> 01:03:52,539
<i>Can you please spread your legs...</i>

787
01:03:52,706 --> 01:03:54,958
<i>...and place your hands
in the yellow circles?</i>

788
01:03:55,125 --> 01:03:57,961
- What are you doing?
- Saving you so you can save the world.

789
01:03:58,128 --> 01:03:59,421
Yeah, but I--

790
01:04:01,173 --> 01:04:03,592
I think this is the door.
There's no name, no number.

791
01:04:03,758 --> 01:04:05,260
Let's see it.

792
01:04:09,598 --> 01:04:11,683
Sir, are you classified as human?

793
01:04:11,850 --> 01:04:14,019
Negative. I am a meat Popsicle.

794
01:04:17,189 --> 01:04:18,523
I found him.

795
01:04:18,690 --> 01:04:20,066
<i>Mr. Korben Dallas?</i>

796
01:04:20,901 --> 01:04:24,696
Sir, can you put your hands
in the yellow circles, please?

797
01:04:27,824 --> 01:04:29,409
Smoke you!

798
01:04:30,410 --> 01:04:32,329
Wrong answer.

799
01:04:34,748 --> 01:04:37,751
<i>The police control is now terminated.</i>

800
01:04:37,918 --> 01:04:41,922
<i>Thank you for your cooperation.
Have a nice day.</i>

801
01:04:42,088 --> 01:04:44,925
Okay. We got the guy.
Wasn't easy, but we bagged him.

802
01:04:45,091 --> 01:04:47,802
<i>- Thanks for the tip.</i>
- Glad to be of help, my friend.

803
01:04:47,969 --> 01:04:50,764
The guy's just been arrested
for uranium smuggling.

804
01:04:50,931 --> 01:04:52,516
Everything's going as planned.

805
01:04:52,682 --> 01:04:55,310
All I have to do is
go to the airport, take his place...

806
01:04:55,477 --> 01:04:58,188
...and I'll be in Fhloston
in less than four hours.

807
01:04:58,355 --> 01:05:00,982
Don't come back without the stones.

808
01:05:17,958 --> 01:05:19,626
Korben Dallas. We got him.

809
01:05:19,793 --> 01:05:20,919
Perfect.

810
01:05:21,086 --> 01:05:23,129
Akanit, take command.

811
01:05:23,713 --> 01:05:26,216
Go to Fhloston and get the stones.

812
01:05:26,383 --> 01:05:28,218
If Zorg really wants them...

813
01:05:28,385 --> 01:05:30,595
...he'll have to negotiate.

814
01:05:30,762 --> 01:05:33,598
Revenge is at hand.

815
01:05:36,601 --> 01:05:40,814
Oh, I am so sorry.
Oh, I forgot about the autowash.

816
01:05:40,981 --> 01:05:43,942
There's an autowash in that shower.

817
01:05:49,155 --> 01:05:50,824
I'm so sorry.

818
01:05:50,991 --> 01:05:52,492
Autowash.

819
01:05:52,659 --> 01:05:56,162
Autowash, yes.
Autowash, in the shower.

820
01:05:56,329 --> 01:05:59,666
Yeah. You know, it's funny.
I've met you twice today.

821
01:05:59,833 --> 01:06:03,044
Both times,
you've ended up in my arms.

822
01:06:03,420 --> 01:06:05,755
It's my lucky day.

823
01:06:06,506 --> 01:06:10,051
Lucky day.

824
01:06:11,052 --> 01:06:12,596
Yeah.

825
01:06:18,518 --> 01:06:20,395
Did you hear something?

826
01:06:20,562 --> 01:06:23,148
Cornelius.

827
01:06:28,528 --> 01:06:29,696
Autowash.

828
01:06:30,947 --> 01:06:32,782
- I'm so sorry.
- I don't need your help.

829
01:06:32,949 --> 01:06:34,326
Sorry.

830
01:06:37,704 --> 01:06:40,457
- Want a cup of coffee? Yeah.
- Yes, please.

831
01:06:40,624 --> 01:06:42,459
Autowash.

832
01:06:43,084 --> 01:06:44,961
Coffee's not really my specialty.

833
01:06:46,463 --> 01:06:50,008
But you must drink a lot of coffee,
being a priest, huh?

834
01:06:56,014 --> 01:06:59,184
I know, I know. I'm not proud
of what I did. I had no choice.

835
01:07:10,570 --> 01:07:12,572
I'll take the mission.

836
01:07:28,922 --> 01:07:30,340
- Did you get them?
- Yeah.

837
01:07:30,507 --> 01:07:32,133
Good.

838
01:07:35,512 --> 01:07:37,347
- "Leeloo Dallas."
- "Multi-pass."

839
01:07:37,514 --> 01:07:39,724
"Korben David Dallas." Perfect.

840
01:07:42,310 --> 01:07:44,688
No, I can't possibly be your husband.
I'm too old.

841
01:07:44,854 --> 01:07:46,606
Now, David is...

842
01:07:47,023 --> 01:07:49,109
...in great shape. He'll protect you.

843
01:07:49,275 --> 01:07:53,697
Now, please, go to the diva, collect
the stones and meet me at the temple.

844
01:07:53,863 --> 01:07:55,865
Now. Yes.

845
01:07:56,616 --> 01:07:58,410
Okay.

846
01:07:58,576 --> 01:08:02,122
<i>Final call for Fhloston Paradise.</i>

847
01:08:02,288 --> 01:08:04,833
Last call for Fhloston Paradise.
Hurry up.

848
01:08:06,209 --> 01:08:07,460
I'm sorry.

849
01:08:07,627 --> 01:08:09,629
The-- The-- The-- The tickets.

850
01:08:09,796 --> 01:08:13,466
- ID, please.
- I'm sorry.

851
01:08:13,800 --> 01:08:16,177
- There.
- In here? All right. Right.

852
01:08:16,344 --> 01:08:17,637
<i>Thank you!</i>

853
01:08:17,804 --> 01:08:19,597
Mr. Dallas?

854
01:08:20,265 --> 01:08:23,476
- Yeah.
- Congratulations on winning the contest.

855
01:08:23,643 --> 01:08:25,478
Oh, right. Okay.

856
01:08:25,645 --> 01:08:27,313
- Sorry for the mess.
- The mess?

857
01:08:27,480 --> 01:08:28,648
The garbage.

858
01:08:29,399 --> 01:08:30,942
Oh, right--

859
01:08:33,361 --> 01:08:34,988
Made it!

860
01:08:35,155 --> 01:08:37,490
I was so afraid I wasn't gonna
make this flight...

861
01:08:37,657 --> 01:08:40,994
...so I sent David here to come
and pick up my boarding pass.

862
01:08:41,161 --> 01:08:44,080
Now David has to go.
Thank you. Bye.

863
01:08:45,039 --> 01:08:47,000
I am Korben Dallas.

864
01:08:47,709 --> 01:08:50,754
<i>Please report infractions
immediately to the spaceport.</i>

865
01:08:50,920 --> 01:08:52,297
And this is?

866
01:08:53,381 --> 01:08:56,009
Leeloo Dallas. Multi-pass.

867
01:08:56,176 --> 01:08:57,427
- Yeah. Leeloo--
- Multi-pass.

868
01:08:57,594 --> 01:09:00,054
She knows it's a multi-pass.
Leeloo Dallas. My wife.

869
01:09:00,221 --> 01:09:02,599
We're newlyweds. Just met.
You know how it is.

870
01:09:02,766 --> 01:09:06,603
Bump into each other, sparks happen--
She knows it's a multi-pass.

871
01:09:06,770 --> 01:09:08,062
Yeah. Anyway, we're in love.

872
01:09:08,855 --> 01:09:12,567
I mean, I know
she's made to be strong.

873
01:09:12,734 --> 01:09:15,987
She's also so fragile, so human.
You know what I mean?

874
01:09:20,533 --> 01:09:23,161
- You want some more?
- Yeah.

875
01:09:26,039 --> 01:09:28,416
- Make that two.
- Hello, David. David.

876
01:09:28,583 --> 01:09:31,002
- Where's Leeloo?
- She's on the plane with Mr. Dallas.

877
01:09:31,669 --> 01:09:33,713
- What?
- I'm sorry. I didn't know what to do.

878
01:09:33,880 --> 01:09:37,425
- I thought he was gonna kill me.
- But this is not possible.

879
01:09:37,592 --> 01:09:39,052
Oh, this is not possible.

880
01:09:39,219 --> 01:09:40,512
You want some more?

881
01:09:40,678 --> 01:09:44,349
This is all my fault.
I am the servant. It is my mission.

882
01:09:44,516 --> 01:09:46,768
- I should never have given it to you.
- I know.

883
01:09:48,603 --> 01:09:50,063
- The key to the temple.
- Oh, no.

884
01:09:50,230 --> 01:09:53,566
Prepare for our arrival.
I go to face my destiny.

885
01:09:53,733 --> 01:09:55,068
Yes.

886
01:09:55,735 --> 01:09:57,904
I don't wanna go to Egypt.

887
01:10:00,365 --> 01:10:01,574
<i>Thank you.</i>

888
01:10:01,741 --> 01:10:03,785
Dallas? Korben Dallas?

889
01:10:05,870 --> 01:10:06,955
Yeah. That's me.

890
01:10:08,248 --> 01:10:10,458
Just a minute, please.

891
01:10:16,089 --> 01:10:18,174
It will take just one more minute.

892
01:10:27,267 --> 01:10:29,686
We'll be right back.

893
01:10:32,814 --> 01:10:35,733
Oh, Mr. Dallas, we really need you now.

894
01:10:35,900 --> 01:10:39,404
Ruby Rhod is broadcasting live,
and he needs you for an interview.

895
01:10:39,571 --> 01:10:40,905
Miss?

896
01:10:41,114 --> 01:10:42,115
Multi-pass.

897
01:10:43,366 --> 01:10:45,994
<i>Alpha Centauri, Flight 194...</i>

898
01:10:46,160 --> 01:10:47,704
Tell Aknot that plan A flopped.

899
01:10:47,871 --> 01:10:49,122
- Go to plan B.
- Okay.

900
01:10:50,623 --> 01:10:52,709
Aliens ahead. Spread out.

901
01:11:02,343 --> 01:11:03,970
Backup unit, Zone 18.

902
01:11:06,848 --> 01:11:09,559
Let's go! Let's go, move!

903
01:11:14,272 --> 01:11:17,191
Mr. Ruby Rhod
is the biggest radio star.

904
01:11:17,358 --> 01:11:19,694
It's a great honor
to be on his talk show.

905
01:11:19,861 --> 01:11:22,655
- He's so green.
- Yes. I'm sure you're very excited.

906
01:11:22,822 --> 01:11:25,116
But I'm on vacation
and don't wanna be bothered.

907
01:11:25,283 --> 01:11:27,368
I prefer to remain anonymous.

908
01:11:30,580 --> 01:11:32,290
Korben Dallas!

909
01:11:32,874 --> 01:11:36,669
Here he is! The one and only winner
of the Gemini Croquette Contest.

910
01:11:36,836 --> 01:11:40,214
This boy is fueled like fire,
so start melting, ladies...

911
01:11:40,381 --> 01:11:43,301
...because the boy is hotter than hot.
He's hot, hot, hot!

912
01:11:45,845 --> 01:11:49,265
The right size, the right build,
the right hair, the right on.

913
01:11:49,515 --> 01:11:50,683
Right on, right on.

914
01:11:50,850 --> 01:11:55,563
And he's got something to say to those
50 billion pairs of ears out there.

915
01:11:56,189 --> 01:11:57,315
Pop it, D-man.

916
01:12:01,694 --> 01:12:04,739
- Hi.
- Unbelievable.

917
01:12:07,241 --> 01:12:09,953
Quiver, ladies. Quiver.
He's gonna set the world on fire.

918
01:12:10,119 --> 01:12:11,537
Right here from 5 to 7.

919
01:12:11,704 --> 01:12:15,249
You'll know everything
there is to know about the D-man.

920
01:12:15,416 --> 01:12:16,793
His dreams...

921
01:12:16,960 --> 01:12:18,336
...his desires...

922
01:12:18,503 --> 01:12:21,214
...his most intimates of intimates.

923
01:12:21,381 --> 01:12:24,509
And from what I'm looking at,
"intimate" is his middle name.

924
01:12:24,676 --> 01:12:27,804
So tell me, my man,
you nervous in the service?

925
01:12:30,765 --> 01:12:32,350
Not really.

926
01:12:32,976 --> 01:12:36,688
Freeze those knees because Korben's
in the place and he's on the case.

927
01:12:36,854 --> 01:12:40,733
Yesterday's frog
will be tomorrow's prince...

928
01:12:40,900 --> 01:12:43,152
...of Fhloston Paradise!

929
01:12:43,319 --> 01:12:46,322
The hotel of a thousand and one
follies and lollies.

930
01:12:46,489 --> 01:12:49,200
A magic fountain flow
of non-stop wine, women and...

931
01:12:49,367 --> 01:12:51,119
...hootchie-kootchie-koo...

932
01:12:51,285 --> 01:12:52,829
...all night long.

933
01:13:02,255 --> 01:13:03,881
Start licking your stamps, girls...

934
01:13:04,048 --> 01:13:06,801
...because this guy's gonna have you
writing home to Mama.

935
01:13:06,968 --> 01:13:09,429
Here, from 5 to 7,
I'll be your voice, your tongue.

936
01:13:09,595 --> 01:13:14,350
I'll be hot on the trail of the sexiest
man of the year: D-man, your man...

937
01:13:17,020 --> 01:13:18,771
...my man.

938
01:13:20,314 --> 01:13:21,899
<i>End of transmission.</i>

939
01:13:22,066 --> 01:13:24,819
<i>Okay, Ruby.
See you tomorrow at 5.</i>

940
01:13:25,361 --> 01:13:26,988
How was it?

941
01:13:28,990 --> 01:13:32,702
- It was just absolutely green.
- I was touched to the core.

942
01:13:32,869 --> 01:13:34,328
Green like what?

943
01:13:34,495 --> 01:13:35,621
- Crystal green.
- Crystal.

944
01:13:35,788 --> 01:13:38,166
- Any kind of green you want.
- Any green you like.

945
01:13:38,332 --> 01:13:41,044
- Tree green, pond green.
- Emerald.

946
01:13:53,181 --> 01:13:56,976
Korben, sweetheart, what was that?
It was bad! It had nothing!

947
01:13:57,143 --> 01:14:00,688
No fire! No energy! No nothing!
You know, I have a show to run here.

948
01:14:00,855 --> 01:14:02,315
And it must pop, pop, pop!

949
01:14:02,482 --> 01:14:03,983
So tomorrow, from 5 to 7...

950
01:14:04,150 --> 01:14:08,154
...will you please act like you have
more than a two-word vocabulary?

951
01:14:08,321 --> 01:14:10,490
It must be green. Okay? Okay?

952
01:14:10,865 --> 01:14:13,743
Can I talk to you for a second?
Can I just talk to you?

953
01:14:14,494 --> 01:14:17,205
I didn't come here to play
Pumba on the radio.

954
01:14:17,371 --> 01:14:20,666
So tomorrow, from 5 to 7,
you're gonna give yourself a hand.

955
01:14:20,833 --> 01:14:23,503
- Green?
- Super-green.

956
01:14:25,171 --> 01:14:26,756
Dallas? Korben Dallas?

957
01:14:26,923 --> 01:14:28,549
That's me.

958
01:14:29,342 --> 01:14:33,930
Listen, I only have one Korben Dallas
on my list, and he's checked in, okay?

959
01:14:36,891 --> 01:14:39,727
That's impossible. I am Korben Dallas.

960
01:14:39,894 --> 01:14:43,189
- Sorry, sir. Boarding is finished.
- Hey.

961
01:14:43,356 --> 01:14:44,565
Wait, wait, wait.

962
01:14:44,732 --> 01:14:46,651
Wait. Hey, hey.

963
01:14:46,818 --> 01:14:48,653
Hey, I need to talk to someone.

964
01:14:48,820 --> 01:14:50,905
I don't believe this!

965
01:14:51,572 --> 01:14:54,742
<i>This is not an exercise.
This is a police control.</i>

966
01:14:54,909 --> 01:14:57,954
- I'm sorry. I'm calm.
<i>- Put your hands in the yellow circle.</i>

967
01:14:58,121 --> 01:14:59,539
There's been a mistake.

968
01:15:00,790 --> 01:15:04,669
To make your flight short, flight attendants
are switching on the sleep regulator...

969
01:15:04,836 --> 01:15:08,214
...which will regulate your sleeping
during the flight.

970
01:15:11,926 --> 01:15:12,969
Thank you.

971
01:15:16,347 --> 01:15:17,390
Hi.

972
01:15:17,557 --> 01:15:20,268
- You speak English now.
- Yes. I learn.

973
01:15:20,434 --> 01:15:21,936
Good.

974
01:15:22,395 --> 01:15:24,230
Leeloo, we are not on vacation.

975
01:15:24,397 --> 01:15:27,900
I'm on a very important mission.
I work for some very important people.

976
01:15:28,067 --> 01:15:31,028
If I hadn't come to get you,
you would be in big trouble.

977
01:15:31,195 --> 01:15:33,614
- Do you understand? Big trouble?
- Yes.

978
01:15:33,781 --> 01:15:36,409
But you, no trouble.

979
01:15:36,826 --> 01:15:39,704
Me, fifth element.

980
01:15:39,871 --> 01:15:42,081
Supreme being.

981
01:15:42,498 --> 01:15:44,959
Me protect you.

982
01:15:47,920 --> 01:15:49,005
Sleep.

983
01:15:52,216 --> 01:15:54,719
- Sweet dreams, Mr. Dallas.
- No, wait--

984
01:15:58,306 --> 01:16:00,600
Sleep regulator operative
in Zone 1, captain.

985
01:16:00,766 --> 01:16:03,102
Thank you.
Zone 2, are you operative?

986
01:16:03,853 --> 01:16:05,146
<i>Zone 2?</i>

987
01:16:05,313 --> 01:16:06,898
Yeah, everything's ready, captain.

988
01:16:07,064 --> 01:16:08,608
- Mr. Rhod.
- What?

989
01:16:08,774 --> 01:16:10,818
You have to assume
your individual position.

990
01:16:10,985 --> 01:16:13,571
I don't want one position.
I want all positions!

991
01:16:14,238 --> 01:16:15,573
Mr. Rhod!

992
01:16:17,366 --> 01:16:19,785
- Parasites in landing gear.
- Ground, you copy?

993
01:16:19,952 --> 01:16:21,579
Got it. Front gear.

994
01:16:21,746 --> 01:16:24,457
Hey, man, give me some heat, man!

995
01:16:24,624 --> 01:16:28,753
We need some heat here, man!
Get some heat!

996
01:16:29,295 --> 01:16:31,589
Some heat over here, man!

997
01:16:31,756 --> 01:16:34,926
Good shit, man.
Put the heat over here, man!

998
01:16:48,564 --> 01:16:52,818
Thank you!
Thank you very much!

999
01:16:55,154 --> 01:16:57,406
Come, come, come.
Give me this. Give me this.

1000
01:17:00,660 --> 01:17:01,827
Take that.

1001
01:17:02,495 --> 01:17:05,122
Mr. Rhod!

1002
01:17:05,665 --> 01:17:07,667
You can call me Ruby.

1003
01:17:08,918 --> 01:17:11,045
Fueled and ready to go.

1004
01:17:11,754 --> 01:17:14,382
- Yep.
- I'll buy you one, man.

1005
01:17:16,634 --> 01:17:18,010
Have you taken off already?

1006
01:17:19,262 --> 01:17:21,806
- I'm not on the plane.
- What?

1007
01:17:21,973 --> 01:17:25,351
The real Dallas took my place.
I don't understand.

1008
01:17:25,518 --> 01:17:26,978
Are you making fun of me?

1009
01:17:27,144 --> 01:17:29,355
No, no, no! I swear! I swear!

1010
01:17:29,522 --> 01:17:32,566
I never felt this way before
with a human.

1011
01:17:33,276 --> 01:17:35,861
- Really?
- Yeah!

1012
01:17:36,028 --> 01:17:39,699
I've tried everything, believe me.
There's no other way to get on the plane.

1013
01:17:47,873 --> 01:17:50,668
- Ground is clear.
- Roger. Ready for liftoff?

1014
01:17:50,835 --> 01:17:52,670
Confirmed.

1015
01:17:57,466 --> 01:18:00,720
Not there. No, please, not there.
No, please, not there. Oh, please.

1016
01:18:00,886 --> 01:18:02,555
- Power pressure?
- Primed.

1017
01:18:07,310 --> 01:18:08,728
- Protection?
- Confirmed.

1018
01:18:09,478 --> 01:18:10,980
Power increase.

1019
01:18:11,147 --> 01:18:12,231
Ten seconds.

1020
01:18:12,398 --> 01:18:14,233
I am...

1021
01:18:14,650 --> 01:18:16,444
...a little...

1022
01:18:16,610 --> 01:18:18,738
- ...disappointed.
- Five...

1023
01:18:18,904 --> 01:18:22,325
- If there is one thing I do not like...
- Three...

1024
01:18:22,491 --> 01:18:24,869
- ...it is to be...
- ...two...

1025
01:18:26,078 --> 01:18:27,872
- ...disappointed.
- ...one.

1026
01:18:28,039 --> 01:18:31,375
- Sorry, sir. This will never happen again.
- I know.

1027
01:18:31,542 --> 01:18:32,585
Liftoff.

1028
01:18:44,180 --> 01:18:47,183
- Landing gear secure.
- Roger. Checklist for light speed.

1029
01:19:13,542 --> 01:19:15,920
Sir, we're finally getting something.

1030
01:19:16,837 --> 01:19:18,464
It's sending radio wavelengths.

1031
01:19:18,631 --> 01:19:22,760
- What does it want with radio waves?
- Maybe it wants to make a call.

1032
01:19:26,514 --> 01:19:28,057
Zorg's office.

1033
01:19:29,225 --> 01:19:31,560
I told you I do not wanna be disturbed.

1034
01:19:31,727 --> 01:19:34,480
You don't want to be disturbed
except if it's Mr. Shadow...

1035
01:19:34,647 --> 01:19:36,690
...and it's Mr. Shadow on the line.

1036
01:19:46,659 --> 01:19:49,078
<i>It's me again.</i>

1037
01:19:49,245 --> 01:19:50,621
Zorg here.

1038
01:19:50,788 --> 01:19:56,419
<i>- Am I disturbing you?</i>
- No, no, I was just--

1039
01:19:57,878 --> 01:19:59,088
Where are you?

1040
01:19:59,880 --> 01:20:02,174
<i>Not far now.</i>

1041
01:20:03,509 --> 01:20:05,094
Good.

1042
01:20:05,261 --> 01:20:06,679
Good, good.

1043
01:20:06,846 --> 01:20:11,225
<i>How are the stones?</i>

1044
01:20:11,392 --> 01:20:15,604
Fine. Fine. Just fine. I'll have the--

1045
01:20:15,771 --> 01:20:19,191
I'll have the four stones
you asked for any time now...

1046
01:20:19,358 --> 01:20:21,110
...but it wasn't easy.

1047
01:20:21,277 --> 01:20:24,405
My costs have tripled.

1048
01:20:24,572 --> 01:20:30,995
<i>Money is of no importance.</i>

1049
01:20:31,162 --> 01:20:37,001
<i>I want the stones.</i>

1050
01:20:37,168 --> 01:20:39,211
The stones...

1051
01:20:40,212 --> 01:20:43,549
...will be here. I'll--

1052
01:20:44,508 --> 01:20:46,343
I'll see to it personally.

1053
01:20:46,510 --> 01:20:50,473
<i>I will be among you...</i>

1054
01:20:50,639 --> 01:20:51,807
<i>...soon.</i>

1055
01:20:55,019 --> 01:20:57,438
- We lost it.
- We lost the signal.

1056
01:20:57,605 --> 01:20:59,148
Damn!

1057
01:21:16,665 --> 01:21:19,835
<i>We've begun our descent
towards Fhloston Paradise.</i>

1058
01:21:20,002 --> 01:21:22,004
<i>The local time is 3:20 p.m.</i>

1059
01:21:22,171 --> 01:21:26,008
<i>Auto-temperature is currently
85 degrees Fahrenheit.</i>

1060
01:21:26,175 --> 01:21:30,513
<i>We hope you've enjoyed your flight for
today and hope to see you again soon.</i>

1061
01:21:48,864 --> 01:21:51,992
<i>Ladies and gentlemen,
welcome to paradise.</i>

1062
01:22:02,836 --> 01:22:05,381
Excuse me, dear. Excuse me.
Thanks. Excuse me, please.

1063
01:22:40,124 --> 01:22:41,959
Parasites in the main ventilation.

1064
01:22:42,126 --> 01:22:43,836
Again? Don't worry. I'll get it.

1065
01:22:52,761 --> 01:22:54,805
Have we arrived yet?

1066
01:22:54,972 --> 01:22:57,433
- Yeah.
- Oh, good.

1067
01:22:58,017 --> 01:23:00,978
We have 12 swimming pools
and two on the rooftop.

1068
01:23:01,145 --> 01:23:04,273
All the restaurants are between
Level 2 and Level 10.

1069
01:23:04,440 --> 01:23:07,985
The planet Fhloston has 400 beaches,
all accessible until 5 p.m.

1070
01:23:09,445 --> 01:23:12,156
Then the airship goes higher
to offer you a better view.

1071
01:23:12,323 --> 01:23:14,450
- Is the diva here yet?
- Not yet.

1072
01:23:14,617 --> 01:23:17,244
Are there any tickets left
for this opera? I'm a big fan.

1073
01:23:17,411 --> 01:23:21,999
You have a seat reserved, front row,
next to Ruby Rhod!

1074
01:23:22,166 --> 01:23:25,210
He's so talented, don't you think?
I just love him. He's so sexy.

1075
01:23:25,377 --> 01:23:29,340
Well, anyway, he has your ticket for the
show, and he'll be here in 20 minutes.

1076
01:23:30,215 --> 01:23:32,301
Do you know where I can get
something to wear?

1077
01:23:35,554 --> 01:23:38,474
- Enjoy your evening, Mr. Dallas.
- Thank you.

1078
01:23:45,522 --> 01:23:47,608
- Hello?
<i>- You miserable bastard.</i>

1079
01:23:47,775 --> 01:23:49,735
<i>- I never should've pushed you out.</i>
- Ma?

1080
01:23:49,902 --> 01:23:52,821
<i>I was in labor for days,
and this is how you repay me?</i>

1081
01:23:52,988 --> 01:23:55,449
<i>- I should've just gotten a robot.</i>
- Come on, Ma.

1082
01:23:55,616 --> 01:23:57,951
<i>Don't "come on, Ma" me.
I should be there, not you.</i>

1083
01:23:58,118 --> 01:24:00,537
<i>I need a tan. I need a cocktail.</i>

1084
01:24:23,268 --> 01:24:24,978
Get the case in.

1085
01:24:28,607 --> 01:24:30,317
Hello, Ms. Diva. I'm Fog.

1086
01:24:30,484 --> 01:24:33,862
Welcome to the-- I'm security. I--

1087
01:24:34,029 --> 01:24:37,157
Welcome to the-- Tall...

1088
01:24:55,634 --> 01:24:57,970
- Can I talk to you for a minute?
- Sure. Yeah.

1089
01:24:58,137 --> 01:25:00,347
- What's your name?
- Fog.

1090
01:25:02,057 --> 01:25:05,394
Ms. Plavalaguna wants you to know
how glad she is that you're here.

1091
01:25:05,561 --> 01:25:09,982
She will give you what you've come
to get after the concert. Stay here.

1092
01:25:11,984 --> 01:25:17,364
<i>You're listening to Radio Cosmos,
and it is now 5 p.m.</i>

1093
01:25:17,531 --> 01:25:19,658
- Helm to 108.
- Yes, sir.

1094
01:25:20,909 --> 01:25:22,327
Helm 108!

1095
01:25:22,494 --> 01:25:23,746
Helm to 108.

1096
01:25:23,912 --> 01:25:28,500
<i>Time to join Ruby Rhod
and Korben Dallas...</i>

1097
01:25:28,667 --> 01:25:33,046
<i>...the lucky winner
of the Gemini Croquette Contest.</i>

1098
01:25:33,213 --> 01:25:36,341
<i>Coming at you live from Fhloston...</i>

1099
01:25:36,508 --> 01:25:37,926
Paradise!

1100
01:25:38,093 --> 01:25:43,015
Ruby Rhod at your service with Korben
and the manager of this green hotel...

1101
01:25:43,182 --> 01:25:46,018
...and Miss Gemini Croquette
in person...

1102
01:25:46,185 --> 01:25:48,270
...and 8000 other lucksters here...

1103
01:25:48,437 --> 01:25:53,233
...to enjoy the privilege of
the unique concert of Miss Plavalaguna!

1104
01:25:56,528 --> 01:26:01,825
And now we enter what must be the most
beautiful concert hall of all the universe!

1105
01:26:01,992 --> 01:26:06,288
A perfect replica
of the old opera house...

1106
01:26:06,455 --> 01:26:08,165
...but who cares?

1107
01:26:08,332 --> 01:26:11,919
To my right, a row of ministers,
more sinisters than ministers.

1108
01:26:12,085 --> 01:26:15,672
To my left, Baby Ray,
star of stage and screen.

1109
01:26:15,839 --> 01:26:19,343
He's not gonna get much out of
this concert because he's stone-deaf!

1110
01:26:19,510 --> 01:26:21,512
To who?

1111
01:26:21,678 --> 01:26:24,848
And here we have Roy Von Bacon,
king of laser ball.

1112
01:26:25,015 --> 01:26:28,644
And here, the emperor of Kodar Japhet
with his lovely daughter.

1113
01:26:28,811 --> 01:26:31,939
"I love to sing,"
she recently confessed to me.

1114
01:26:32,105 --> 01:26:35,692
By the way, I have a recording
of her talented voice.

1115
01:26:36,527 --> 01:26:40,197
I play the rest of the songs after the
concert because right now it's time...

1116
01:26:40,364 --> 01:26:42,574
...for Korben
to say the word of the day.

1117
01:26:43,116 --> 01:26:47,663
Tell me, my man,
you happy here in the big world?

1118
01:26:47,830 --> 01:26:51,667
- I find it boring, really.
- Thrilled.

1119
01:26:51,834 --> 01:26:54,795
And now champagne!

1120
01:27:00,884 --> 01:27:03,303
Commercial! Commercial!

1121
01:27:03,470 --> 01:27:05,055
<i>Break for 30 seconds.</i>

1122
01:27:21,530 --> 01:27:22,990
Showtime.

1123
01:29:15,268 --> 01:29:18,939
Commander, I have a ship in trouble
requesting permission to dock for repairs.

1124
01:29:19,106 --> 01:29:22,401
Put him in the docking garage.
Inform security.

1125
01:29:22,567 --> 01:29:25,278
<i>- Permission granted for one hour.</i>
- More than I need.

1126
01:29:39,042 --> 01:29:42,629
- Yes?
- Champagne for the diva.

1127
01:29:42,796 --> 01:29:44,756
I'll take it.

1128
01:30:18,957 --> 01:30:20,459
I found it.

1129
01:30:55,410 --> 01:30:56,411
Get her!

1130
01:32:30,589 --> 01:32:31,965
It was an ambush.

1131
01:32:35,802 --> 01:32:40,098
If it's war they want,
it's war they'll get!

1132
01:32:42,934 --> 01:32:44,769
Bravo! Bravo!

1133
01:32:44,936 --> 01:32:47,105
Bravo. Bravo.

1134
01:32:47,272 --> 01:32:48,857
My compliments, little lady.

1135
01:32:49,024 --> 01:32:53,361
Thank you for doing all the dirty work.
I couldn't have done a better job myself.

1136
01:32:54,112 --> 01:32:55,280
Hand over the stones.

1137
01:33:35,779 --> 01:33:37,989
Nobody move! I'm taking over the ship!

1138
01:33:42,661 --> 01:33:44,204
Hands up!

1139
01:33:58,677 --> 01:34:00,845
Ruby! Ruby!

1140
01:34:52,314 --> 01:34:54,316
I know this music.

1141
01:34:56,234 --> 01:34:58,611
Let's change the beat.

1142
01:35:04,743 --> 01:35:06,995
Ladies and gentlemen,
I think we're being attacked.

1143
01:35:07,162 --> 01:35:09,456
<i>I don't know who they are,
but they're everywhere.</i>

1144
01:35:09,622 --> 01:35:11,750
<i>I see one. They're warriors,
and they're ugly.</i>

1145
01:35:11,916 --> 01:35:15,086
<i>They got big teeth, big foreheads
and big ears, and they stink.</i>

1146
01:35:15,253 --> 01:35:16,254
Mangalores.

1147
01:35:19,090 --> 01:35:21,509
The government sent me to help you.
Just stay calm.

1148
01:35:21,676 --> 01:35:25,764
If somebody hear this,
come and get me. I'm in the first row.

1149
01:35:27,891 --> 01:35:30,560
- You must give her the stones.
- Who?

1150
01:35:30,727 --> 01:35:32,562
The fifth element.

1151
01:35:32,729 --> 01:35:36,941
The supreme being sent to Earth
to save the universe.

1152
01:35:37,108 --> 01:35:39,611
- Leeloo?
- Yes.

1153
01:35:40,487 --> 01:35:44,157
But she's more fragile than she seems.

1154
01:35:44,407 --> 01:35:46,701
She needs your help...

1155
01:35:47,118 --> 01:35:48,453
...and your love...

1156
01:35:49,287 --> 01:35:53,291
...or she will die.

1157
01:35:56,920 --> 01:36:00,048
- No, no, no. Stay with me.
- Help!

1158
01:36:06,805 --> 01:36:11,142
If you want something done,
do it yourself.

1159
01:36:11,726 --> 01:36:15,146
Come on, honey. You can't die.
Come on. Listen to me. Wake up!

1160
01:36:15,313 --> 01:36:16,898
- Where are the stones?
- What?

1161
01:36:17,065 --> 01:36:19,651
The stones. Where are the stones?

1162
01:36:19,818 --> 01:36:20,860
The stones.

1163
01:36:34,666 --> 01:36:36,793
They're not here.

1164
01:36:37,335 --> 01:36:39,421
The stones, where are they?

1165
01:36:41,089 --> 01:36:42,799
In me.

1166
01:36:42,966 --> 01:36:44,843
What? What?

1167
01:36:51,099 --> 01:36:54,310
Oh, my God. Korben. Oh, my God.
Korben, Korben, another one coming.

1168
01:36:54,477 --> 01:36:57,230
- Korben, we should go.
- One minute. Just give me a minute.

1169
01:36:57,397 --> 01:36:59,065
Hey, you!

1170
01:36:59,607 --> 01:37:01,234
I said you.

1171
01:37:01,401 --> 01:37:03,862
- I'm not with him.
- Where's the other?

1172
01:37:06,197 --> 01:37:07,657
I said one minute.

1173
01:37:07,824 --> 01:37:09,409
- Ruby, hold this gun.
- What?

1174
01:37:09,576 --> 01:37:10,994
What-- What you want me to do?

1175
01:37:11,161 --> 01:37:13,788
- Come on. Put your hand on it. Got it?
- Oh, my God.

1176
01:37:13,955 --> 01:37:16,249
- What do I do?
- If he moves, squeeze the trigger.

1177
01:37:18,251 --> 01:37:22,755
- I don't feel right. I don't feel right.
- The stones are in me.

1178
01:37:32,015 --> 01:37:34,267
Korben, I got a headache.
Korben, this ain't me.

1179
01:37:49,115 --> 01:37:50,116
Ruby--

1180
01:37:52,869 --> 01:37:54,996
Sorry. Sorry. Sorry.

1181
01:37:55,413 --> 01:37:57,248
Think he's gonna be okay?

1182
01:38:03,796 --> 01:38:06,424
Oh, my God. Oh, my God, Korben.
Another one coming.

1183
01:38:08,927 --> 01:38:10,762
Shit. Three coming, Korben. Three.

1184
01:38:13,973 --> 01:38:18,394
Listen, you guard this with your life,
or you'll look like this guy. You green?

1185
01:38:18,561 --> 01:38:19,896
- Green.
<i>- Super-green?</i>

1186
01:38:20,063 --> 01:38:23,191
<i>- Super-green.</i>
- Is that your idea of a discreet operation?

1187
01:38:23,358 --> 01:38:27,153
Don't worry, sir. I know my man.
He'll calm things down.

1188
01:38:40,500 --> 01:38:41,501
Right.

1189
01:38:54,472 --> 01:38:56,307
Move! Move!

1190
01:38:57,600 --> 01:38:59,143
Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

1191
01:38:59,310 --> 01:39:02,146
Ladies and gentlemen--
Ladies and gentlemen, this is amazing.

1192
01:39:04,190 --> 01:39:06,568
Let me do it.

1193
01:39:13,116 --> 01:39:14,701
Oh, my God. Korben Dallas.

1194
01:39:14,867 --> 01:39:17,287
Korben, my man.
Korben Dallas is in trouble.

1195
01:39:19,330 --> 01:39:21,165
Hey. Ray!

1196
01:39:23,543 --> 01:39:25,128
The gun.

1197
01:39:26,129 --> 01:39:27,964
Give me the gun. The gun. The gun!

1198
01:39:28,131 --> 01:39:33,678
I'm gonna go and try to see
if I can see something a little closer.

1199
01:39:50,320 --> 01:39:52,030
Yes, the gun. Yeah.

1200
01:40:01,623 --> 01:40:03,082
Thanks, Ray.

1201
01:40:03,458 --> 01:40:07,003
Don't shoot! Don't shoot!
Don't shoot! I'm not armed!

1202
01:40:07,170 --> 01:40:08,212
Get up!

1203
01:40:08,379 --> 01:40:10,757
You've got the wrong guy! Don't shoot!

1204
01:40:10,923 --> 01:40:12,258
I'm not armed. I'm not armed!

1205
01:40:16,179 --> 01:40:18,640
- Oh, my God.
- I'm on vacation. It's--

1206
01:40:18,806 --> 01:40:22,894
I'm on-- Don't shoot me, please.
I'm on a vacation. I won a...

1207
01:40:24,187 --> 01:40:25,313
...contest.

1208
01:40:25,480 --> 01:40:28,983
Gemini Croquette's
to Fhloston Paradise.

1209
01:40:31,694 --> 01:40:33,321
Down.

1210
01:40:34,739 --> 01:40:36,824
- Wait a minute. Wait a minute.
- Get down!

1211
01:40:38,993 --> 01:40:41,579
- He's trying to say something to me.
- Get down!

1212
01:40:42,121 --> 01:40:43,706
Okay.

1213
01:40:56,177 --> 01:40:57,345
Sorry. Sorry, my man.

1214
01:40:57,512 --> 01:40:59,138
Sorry.

1215
01:41:04,977 --> 01:41:06,521
Korben. Korben.

1216
01:41:07,105 --> 01:41:08,898
Where are you, man?

1217
01:41:09,357 --> 01:41:10,441
Oh, my God.

1218
01:41:10,608 --> 01:41:11,943
Oh, my God. Oh, Korben.

1219
01:41:12,110 --> 01:41:14,362
They're coming.
Korben, they're coming.

1220
01:41:16,656 --> 01:41:17,657
Korben!

1221
01:41:18,825 --> 01:41:20,118
- Don't move.
- What?

1222
01:41:30,628 --> 01:41:33,548
- What you doing?
- Count to 10.

1223
01:41:41,347 --> 01:41:43,683
- Korben, was that a bomb?
- What? Shut up and count!

1224
01:41:43,850 --> 01:41:46,811
One, two, three, four, five...

1225
01:41:46,978 --> 01:41:49,272
...six, seven, eight...

1226
01:41:50,356 --> 01:41:51,774
...nine...

1227
01:42:15,882 --> 01:42:17,175
Ten.

1228
01:42:23,139 --> 01:42:27,018
I am very disappointed!

1229
01:42:27,685 --> 01:42:29,854
Korben. Korben,
what are you looking for?

1230
01:42:30,021 --> 01:42:31,230
Control room.

1231
01:42:33,232 --> 01:42:34,692
- This is it.
- I'll be over here.

1232
01:42:34,859 --> 01:42:36,486
Let's go! Let's go!

1233
01:42:39,822 --> 01:42:42,408
Quiet! Quiet!

1234
01:42:42,825 --> 01:42:45,244
- You in charge?
- Yeah.

1235
01:42:45,411 --> 01:42:47,330
How many of them are out there?

1236
01:42:47,872 --> 01:42:49,999
- I don't know.
- Let's count.

1237
01:42:53,002 --> 01:42:55,421
Seven on the left. Five on the right.

1238
01:43:01,552 --> 01:43:03,513
Four on the right. Two on the left.

1239
01:43:04,847 --> 01:43:07,600
Find the leader.
They won't fight without the leader.

1240
01:43:08,142 --> 01:43:10,520
One more shot,
and we start killing hostages.

1241
01:43:11,646 --> 01:43:14,816
- That's the leader.
- Send someone to negotiate.

1242
01:43:16,442 --> 01:43:19,320
I-- I-- I-- I've never negotiated. I--

1243
01:43:19,570 --> 01:43:21,489
You mind if I try?

1244
01:43:21,656 --> 01:43:23,407
No, no. Sure, sure. Sure.

1245
01:43:23,574 --> 01:43:26,410
We're sending somebody in
to negotiate!

1246
01:43:34,961 --> 01:43:37,046
Anybody else wanna negotiate?

1247
01:43:37,213 --> 01:43:39,882
Where did he learn
to negotiate like that?

1248
01:43:40,383 --> 01:43:41,759
I wonder.

1249
01:43:46,389 --> 01:43:48,224
Where's Ruby?

1250
01:43:48,599 --> 01:43:50,101
I thought he was dead.

1251
01:43:50,268 --> 01:43:51,310
Master!

1252
01:43:51,477 --> 01:43:54,605
It was nothing, really.
It was just a helping hand.

1253
01:43:55,106 --> 01:43:57,525
Ladies and gentlemen,
this is Ruby Rhod...

1254
01:43:57,692 --> 01:43:59,735
...still alive.

1255
01:43:59,902 --> 01:44:03,030
What's wrong with you? It hurt!

1256
01:44:08,452 --> 01:44:12,290
Korben, I realize that
you must be pretty mad at me...

1257
01:44:12,456 --> 01:44:14,876
...but know that I am fighting
for a noble cause.

1258
01:44:15,042 --> 01:44:18,379
Yes, you're trying to save the world.
I remember.

1259
01:44:18,546 --> 01:44:21,632
- Right now, I'm trying to save Leeloo.
- Leeloo's in trouble?

1260
01:44:21,799 --> 01:44:23,426
When is Leeloo not in trouble?

1261
01:44:23,593 --> 01:44:25,928
- There. Where is that?
- That's the diva's suite.

1262
01:44:26,679 --> 01:44:28,306
Leeloo.

1263
01:44:30,016 --> 01:44:31,642
Leeloo.

1264
01:44:31,934 --> 01:44:33,102
Hang on.

1265
01:44:35,771 --> 01:44:39,066
All right, here, come on. How do you
get yourself into these positions?

1266
01:44:40,443 --> 01:44:42,028
Come on.

1267
01:44:44,739 --> 01:44:48,075
Yeah, I'm here. It's all right.
It's all right. Everything's okay now.

1268
01:44:48,242 --> 01:44:49,744
Listen.

1269
01:44:51,871 --> 01:44:54,874
I got the stones. All right?
Just take it easy. All right?

1270
01:44:57,543 --> 01:45:01,964
My man, my man, my man, what's
this thing with all these numbers?

1271
01:45:07,178 --> 01:45:09,305
It's-- It's-- It's--

1272
01:45:09,472 --> 01:45:11,474
No, no, no.

1273
01:45:11,641 --> 01:45:13,100
Because if it was a bomb...

1274
01:45:13,267 --> 01:45:17,980
...the alarms would go off because all
these hotels have bomb detectors. Right?

1275
01:45:19,482 --> 01:45:21,651
<i>This is a Type A alert.</i>

1276
01:45:21,817 --> 01:45:25,363
<i>For security reasons,
the hotel must be evacuated.</i>

1277
01:45:26,614 --> 01:45:29,241
<i>- Please proceed calmly to the lifeboats...</i>
- Stay calm!

1278
01:45:29,408 --> 01:45:31,577
<i>...located in the main hallways.</i>

1279
01:45:31,744 --> 01:45:32,912
Please, stay calm!

1280
01:45:37,500 --> 01:45:39,669
- Look out!
- Korben. Korben, my man.

1281
01:45:39,835 --> 01:45:41,837
You know how to stop this, right?

1282
01:45:43,381 --> 01:45:44,966
Korben?

1283
01:45:47,009 --> 01:45:50,596
<i>Two minutes to complete evacuation.</i>

1284
01:45:52,306 --> 01:45:55,059
- Get back!
- Evacuation! Evacuation!

1285
01:45:55,226 --> 01:45:58,604
Sorry, sir, you can't stay here.
There's a bomb in the hotel.

1286
01:46:03,526 --> 01:46:05,111
I know.

1287
01:46:19,750 --> 01:46:21,460
- I don't want to die.
- Please, my son.

1288
01:46:21,627 --> 01:46:25,047
- I don't want to die.
- Get in.

1289
01:46:29,260 --> 01:46:32,680
<i>One minute to total evacuation.</i>

1290
01:46:37,184 --> 01:46:38,519
This one.

1291
01:46:41,230 --> 01:46:43,649
<i>Forty-five seconds.</i>

1292
01:46:46,318 --> 01:46:47,945
Get her strapped in.

1293
01:46:52,950 --> 01:46:55,661
Korben, Korben, my man,
you know how to fly this thing?

1294
01:46:55,828 --> 01:46:57,079
Just like driving a cab.

1295
01:47:01,792 --> 01:47:03,669
But how we gonna get out the door?

1296
01:47:17,183 --> 01:47:20,186
<i>Fifteen seconds.</i>

1297
01:47:23,814 --> 01:47:27,610
<i>Ten, nine, eight...</i>

1298
01:47:27,777 --> 01:47:32,531
<i>...seven, six, five...</i>

1299
01:47:48,798 --> 01:47:51,008
For the honor.

1300
01:47:54,637 --> 01:47:55,721
Oh, no.

1301
01:47:56,764 --> 01:47:58,057
You should hold on.

1302
01:48:20,037 --> 01:48:21,247
Like driving a cab.

1303
01:48:23,249 --> 01:48:25,918
Ladies and gentlemen,
it is now 7 p.m. Time for the news.

1304
01:48:26,085 --> 01:48:28,254
See you tomorrow for a new adventure.

1305
01:48:28,420 --> 01:48:30,589
<i>End of transmission.</i>

1306
01:48:31,048 --> 01:48:33,551
That's the best show I ever did.

1307
01:48:35,803 --> 01:48:38,639
Mr. President, Major Dallas
has the five elements on board...

1308
01:48:38,806 --> 01:48:41,976
...and the priest is guiding them
directly to the temple.

1309
01:48:46,188 --> 01:48:47,481
We're saved.

1310
01:49:03,747 --> 01:49:06,709
The diva said that
I should take care of you.

1311
01:49:07,459 --> 01:49:10,004
Humans act so strange.

1312
01:49:10,171 --> 01:49:11,797
What do you mean?

1313
01:49:13,090 --> 01:49:15,134
Everything you created...

1314
01:49:15,301 --> 01:49:16,844
...is used to destroy.

1315
01:49:17,303 --> 01:49:18,888
Yeah.

1316
01:49:19,138 --> 01:49:22,808
We call it human nature.
You learn about that on your screen?

1317
01:49:22,975 --> 01:49:24,894
I'm not finished yet.

1318
01:49:25,060 --> 01:49:26,228
I'm up to V.

1319
01:49:26,437 --> 01:49:28,272
V is good.

1320
01:49:28,439 --> 01:49:30,316
Some very good words in V.

1321
01:49:30,482 --> 01:49:31,901
Like what?

1322
01:49:34,111 --> 01:49:35,821
Valiant.

1323
01:49:35,988 --> 01:49:37,948
Vulnerable.

1324
01:49:39,658 --> 01:49:41,952
Very beautiful.

1325
01:49:46,624 --> 01:49:48,500
Yes!

1326
01:49:50,502 --> 01:49:51,670
Yes.

1327
01:49:53,130 --> 01:49:56,091
Oh, of course, Munro!

1328
01:49:56,967 --> 01:49:59,386
- Mr. President?
- Yes, now what?

1329
01:49:59,595 --> 01:50:01,222
I-- I--

1330
01:50:02,681 --> 01:50:04,099
We have a problem.

1331
01:50:09,521 --> 01:50:12,149
- What do you mean, it's advancing?
- Not only advancing...

1332
01:50:12,316 --> 01:50:15,569
...it's moving at incredible speed.
We're having trouble following it.

1333
01:50:19,156 --> 01:50:22,576
And do you have any idea
where it's heading?

1334
01:50:29,500 --> 01:50:32,336
Korben, there's a general
on the phone.

1335
01:50:33,003 --> 01:50:35,297
I'll give you to the president.

1336
01:50:36,048 --> 01:50:39,009
Major Dallas, I, first,
would like to salute a warrior.

1337
01:50:39,176 --> 01:50:41,262
<i>You're a shining example
of this army's might.</i>

1338
01:50:41,428 --> 01:50:43,681
- Mr. President--
<i>- In the name of the Federation--</i>

1339
01:50:43,847 --> 01:50:46,517
Any idea when
you're gonna be getting to the point?

1340
01:50:48,060 --> 01:50:52,815
Okay. There's a ball of fire 1200 miles
in diameter heading straight for Earth...

1341
01:50:52,982 --> 01:50:56,735
<i>...and we have no idea how to stop it.
That's the problem.</i>

1342
01:50:59,697 --> 01:51:01,115
How much time do we have?

1343
01:51:02,199 --> 01:51:05,661
If its speed remains constant,
in an hour and 57 minutes.

1344
01:51:06,745 --> 01:51:08,706
I'll call you back in two hours.

1345
01:51:08,872 --> 01:51:09,873
Hello?

1346
01:51:10,040 --> 01:51:11,834
Hello? Hello?

1347
01:52:22,279 --> 01:52:23,739
They just landed in the desert.

1348
01:52:26,075 --> 01:52:28,077
Good job, David.

1349
01:52:29,328 --> 01:52:32,206
- Put her in the center.
- Where? Here?

1350
01:52:39,254 --> 01:52:44,093
- You got it figured out, Father?
- This one should be fire.

1351
01:52:44,259 --> 01:52:46,387
- You know how this works?
- Theoretically, yes.

1352
01:52:46,553 --> 01:52:51,683
The four stones should go around. The
fifth element should be in the middle...

1353
01:52:51,850 --> 01:52:55,229
...and then the weapon
against evil should work.

1354
01:52:55,604 --> 01:52:58,774
- You've never seen this work before?
- No.

1355
01:52:59,108 --> 01:53:02,778
Every weapon has a manual.
I'm sure this has one too.

1356
01:53:10,869 --> 01:53:13,789
That's it. That's it.
Match up the symbols. Go! Go!

1357
01:53:15,290 --> 01:53:16,792
Wind.

1358
01:53:18,210 --> 01:53:19,962
My man, what you doing?

1359
01:53:20,129 --> 01:53:22,589
- What?
- What you doing?

1360
01:53:23,465 --> 01:53:25,259
Trying to keep you in the DJ business.

1361
01:53:29,096 --> 01:53:30,514
Fire.

1362
01:53:31,640 --> 01:53:32,724
Done.

1363
01:53:32,891 --> 01:53:37,020
- So, what happens now?
- So now, we have to open them.

1364
01:53:37,855 --> 01:53:41,275
- And you know how to do that. Right?
- Theoretically...

1365
01:53:42,860 --> 01:53:43,861
- ...no.
- No.

1366
01:53:48,907 --> 01:53:51,660
Leeloo, wake up, honey. Wake up.
You have to help us.

1367
01:53:51,827 --> 01:53:54,496
Leeloo, how do you open these stones?

1368
01:53:55,914 --> 01:53:58,333
Wind blows.

1369
01:53:59,334 --> 01:54:00,711
Fire burns.

1370
01:54:00,878 --> 01:54:04,256
Yes. Yes, I know all that.
But how do you open these stones?

1371
01:54:04,756 --> 01:54:06,592
Rain...

1372
01:54:09,219 --> 01:54:11,346
...falls.

1373
01:54:11,513 --> 01:54:13,015
What?

1374
01:54:14,266 --> 01:54:15,851
Leeloo. Leeloo.

1375
01:54:18,020 --> 01:54:19,855
What does it mean?

1376
01:54:20,522 --> 01:54:21,690
I think that--

1377
01:54:21,857 --> 01:54:23,358
- Maybe it's a charade.
- What?

1378
01:54:23,525 --> 01:54:24,693
A game or something.

1379
01:54:25,277 --> 01:54:27,797
If we don't get these stones open
in five minutes, we're all dead.

1380
01:54:27,821 --> 01:54:29,323
- Dead?
- Yes, dead.

1381
01:54:42,127 --> 01:54:43,837
Too late.

1382
01:54:45,214 --> 01:54:48,759
- We've lost contact with them.
- Three minutes.

1383
01:54:49,718 --> 01:54:52,721
I think mine is broken.
Why I gotta get the broke one?

1384
01:55:01,396 --> 01:55:03,357
We're never gonna make it.

1385
01:55:07,945 --> 01:55:10,948
Korben. Korben, it moved!

1386
01:55:12,074 --> 01:55:14,368
- What'd you do? Show me what you did.
- Nothing.

1387
01:55:14,535 --> 01:55:15,911
Shut up, shut up!

1388
01:55:16,078 --> 01:55:19,373
Shut up! Calm down.
Show me what you did, step by step.

1389
01:55:19,540 --> 01:55:21,250
- I was just standing here.
- Quickly.

1390
01:55:21,416 --> 01:55:26,213
Okay, and I put my hands on the top
like this, and I said:

1391
01:55:26,755 --> 01:55:28,757
"We're not gonna make it."

1392
01:55:30,425 --> 01:55:32,010
And that's it?

1393
01:55:38,892 --> 01:55:42,020
Korben. Korben, my man.

1394
01:55:42,437 --> 01:55:43,939
Wind.

1395
01:55:44,314 --> 01:55:47,317
She said, "Wind blows."

1396
01:55:54,366 --> 01:55:56,118
Everyone take a stone.

1397
01:55:56,285 --> 01:55:59,121
Water for water. Fire for fire.
Earth for earth. Go, now.

1398
01:56:01,582 --> 01:56:02,791
Earth.

1399
01:56:02,958 --> 01:56:04,793
- Open the other one.
- Okay.

1400
01:56:18,974 --> 01:56:20,267
Korben?

1401
01:56:20,434 --> 01:56:22,728
Korben, my man, I have no fire.

1402
01:56:22,894 --> 01:56:25,105
I mean, I have no matches.
You have any matches?

1403
01:56:25,272 --> 01:56:27,649
I stopped smoking. If I knew...
Father, you smoke?

1404
01:56:27,816 --> 01:56:31,361
Give me some-- Got some matches?
Matches? We need some fire.

1405
01:56:31,945 --> 01:56:33,822
We gonna die.

1406
01:56:40,871 --> 01:56:42,164
Don't breathe.

1407
01:57:01,475 --> 01:57:02,934
Fire.

1408
01:57:03,101 --> 01:57:04,353
One minute.

1409
01:57:04,519 --> 01:57:06,063
Let's go. Let's go, Leeloo.

1410
01:57:06,229 --> 01:57:09,775
Wake up. Wake up.
It's time for you to work now.

1411
01:57:09,983 --> 01:57:11,943
Protect life...

1412
01:57:12,861 --> 01:57:14,029
- ...until death.
- No.

1413
01:57:14,196 --> 01:57:17,032
No! Leeloo, Leeloo, listen to me!
Listen to me. Listen.

1414
01:57:17,199 --> 01:57:20,035
Listen, I know you're very tired.
I know you're very tired.

1415
01:57:20,202 --> 01:57:23,955
I'll take you on a vacation when we're
done. A real vacation, just you and me.

1416
01:57:24,122 --> 01:57:27,501
But listen to me, if you don't
do something right now, we'll all die.

1417
01:57:27,668 --> 01:57:31,505
What's the use of saving life
when you see what you do with it?

1418
01:57:31,672 --> 01:57:34,216
It'll be entering the atmosphere
in 40 seconds.

1419
01:57:35,759 --> 01:57:39,388
Leeloo, you're right, you're right,
you're right. But there are some things--

1420
01:57:39,554 --> 01:57:42,099
Very nice things worth saving,
some beautiful things.

1421
01:57:42,599 --> 01:57:44,810
Beautiful things.

1422
01:57:45,394 --> 01:57:46,895
Like love?

1423
01:57:47,062 --> 01:57:48,980
Yes. Yes, love.
That's good. That's good.

1424
01:57:49,147 --> 01:57:51,983
That's a good example.
Like love. Love is worth saving.

1425
01:57:52,484 --> 01:57:54,695
I don't know love.

1426
01:57:56,321 --> 01:57:57,698
I don't know love.

1427
01:57:57,864 --> 01:58:00,158
I was built to protect, not to love.

1428
01:58:00,325 --> 01:58:02,661
So there's no use for me
other than this.

1429
01:58:02,828 --> 01:58:05,831
No, no, no, you're wrong.
You're wrong. You're wrong.

1430
01:58:06,415 --> 01:58:09,960
I need you. I need you, very much.

1431
01:58:11,169 --> 01:58:12,379
Why?

1432
01:58:14,297 --> 01:58:15,799
Because...

1433
01:58:15,966 --> 01:58:17,884
Because...

1434
01:58:18,260 --> 01:58:20,762
Tell her, Korben.

1435
01:58:22,305 --> 01:58:24,850
Tell me. Please.

1436
01:58:25,016 --> 01:58:27,102
Why do you need me?

1437
01:58:27,394 --> 01:58:30,897
- Because...
- Tell me.

1438
01:58:32,649 --> 01:58:34,192
- Tell me.
- Because I--

1439
01:58:34,359 --> 01:58:36,361
Because I love you.

1440
01:58:37,070 --> 01:58:38,780
I love you.

1441
01:58:42,409 --> 01:58:46,872
Ten, nine, eight, seven...

1442
01:58:47,038 --> 01:58:50,584
...six, five, four, three...

1443
01:58:51,168 --> 01:58:53,253
...two, one.

1444
01:59:31,333 --> 01:59:35,504
<i>Scanner imaging has confirmed
the dark planet dead.</i>

1445
01:59:36,129 --> 01:59:38,965
The planet seems to have stopped
at 62 miles from impact.

1446
01:59:50,560 --> 01:59:51,686
Yes!

1447
01:59:51,853 --> 01:59:53,980
What's wrong with you?
What you screaming for?

1448
01:59:54,147 --> 01:59:56,858
Every five minutes, there's something,
a bomb or something.

1449
01:59:57,025 --> 01:59:58,568
I'm leaving.

1450
02:00:12,833 --> 02:00:14,042
Mr. President.

1451
02:00:14,209 --> 02:00:16,920
Let me introduce Professor Mactilburgh
who runs the center.

1452
02:00:17,087 --> 02:00:18,880
It's an honor, Mr. President.

1453
02:00:19,047 --> 02:00:20,257
Where are my two heroes?

1454
02:00:21,132 --> 02:00:24,678
Well, they were so tired from their
ordeal, we put them in the reactor.

1455
02:00:24,886 --> 02:00:26,763
I have 19 more meetings after this.

1456
02:00:26,930 --> 02:00:29,391
Yeah. I'm sorry.
Let me see if they're revived.

1457
02:00:29,558 --> 02:00:30,725
Thank you.

1458
02:00:30,892 --> 02:00:33,520
We go live in one minute,
Mr. President.

1459
02:00:41,278 --> 02:00:42,904
They're...

1460
02:00:44,030 --> 02:00:45,782
...not ready.

1461
02:00:46,283 --> 02:00:47,409
They need...

1462
02:00:47,576 --> 02:00:50,287
- ...five more minutes.
- You have 20 seconds.

1463
02:00:50,453 --> 02:00:52,747
No, ma'am. No. No, no, I tried.
No, ma'am.

1464
02:00:52,914 --> 02:00:54,416
- Who's that?
- Some woman.

1465
02:00:54,583 --> 02:00:57,419
- Claims to be Korben's mother.
- Well, give it here.

1466
02:00:58,128 --> 02:01:02,799
Mrs. Dallas, this is the president.
On behalf of the Federation--

1467
02:01:02,966 --> 02:01:04,759
<i>That doesn't even sound like him.</i>

1468
02:01:04,926 --> 02:01:07,512
<i>The president's an idiot.
You don't sound like an idiot.</i>

1469
02:01:07,679 --> 02:01:10,265
<i>Don't wanna talk to your mother,
avoid me like usual.</i>

1470
02:01:10,432 --> 02:01:14,978
<i>I'll just throw myself in traffic. I'll
just Saran Wrap myself to the bed and...</i>

